title: pineapple slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Mix egg, sugar, baking powder, flour, milk, and vanilla.
Put in bottom of cake pan.

title: jambalaya
directions: Remove skin from chicken, if desired.
Place chicken, water, salt and pepper in Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Skim fat from broth, then strain broth.

title: cinnamon raisin biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl; cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add raisins; toss well.
Add 3/4 cup milk; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a heavily floured surface; knead dough 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to a 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 11 minutes, or until golden.
Combine powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon milk; stir well.
Drizzle over biscuits.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together and put in loaf pans or coffee cans.
Fill half full.
Spray container with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Check with toothpick to see if done.

title: quakers
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add with oatmeal in batter.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients well. Add the melted butter, vanilla and coconut.
Blend well. Butter 2 pie plates and pour mixture in them.
(Makes its own pie crust.)
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. When cold it slices real well.

title: moody loaf cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer at one time and set on slow speed until mixed well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon twist coffeecake
directions: In a large bowl thoroughly mix 1 3/4 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and undissolved dry yeast.
Combine milk, water and 1/4 cup margarine in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Margarine does not need to melt. Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in raisins and enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap, then a towel.
Let rest 20 minutes.
Divide dough in half. Roll out each half into a 12-inch square.
Brush lightly with melted margarine.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients, except potato chips.
Spread in baking dish.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: With mixer, beat together cake mix, eggs, oil, water, pudding mix and sour cream; blend well.
Add nuts, vanilla and chocolate chips by hand.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Cover with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, margarine and vanilla until fluffy.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over cooled cake.
May sprinkle with chopped nuts if desired.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Sift together next 7 ingredients and stir into pumpkin mixture.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium size bowl.
Insert popsicle stick in one end of each wiener.
Dip in mixture.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: edith harris' almond crusted trout
directions: Salt and pepper fish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread over skin side of fish.
Bake at 400° until fish flakes with fork.

title: chicken-n-dressing casserole
directions: Melt butter and add stuffing mix and onion.
Add other ingredients; mix.
Put some of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in oblong pan.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: bill's chicken patti delight
directions: Take 2 chicken patties and nuke them for 3 minutes, then take 1 or 2 slices of cheese and put them on the patties.
Re-nuke them for an additional 20 seconds.
Mix up the buttermilk dressing and then pour over the patties.
Go fir it!!

title: kay's artichoke-parmesan spread
directions: Cut hearts into bite size pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to hearts.
Bake in serving dish at 350°.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: cake in a jar
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs; add bananas, then milk.
Sift flour and soda.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Bake in wide mouth canning jar.
Spray inside of jar with Pam. Fill jar a little over 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° until done.
Check with toothpick.
Place lid on jar while hot and immediately turn upside down to cool.
This will seal jars.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Place in buttered baking dish. Top with potato chip crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken barbecue sauce (low calorie)
directions: Cook in saucepan until thick (20 minutes).

title: economical brownies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream well.
Add melted chocolate. Add egg and vanilla to milk.
Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder and sift again.
Add nuts to flour mixture.
Combine the two mixtures and pour in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen in
water
to	cover
until
tender.
Cool and debone.
Reserve broth.
Brown onions, green pepper and celery in butter.
Add
garlic
powder, chili powder and pepper.
Add soup, water and chicken;	simmer about 1 hour.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth
until
done.
Add chicken mixture and simmer about 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a casserole pan (9 x 9-inch).
Combine sugar, flour, milk and fluid; pour over melted butter.
Spoon cut up peaches on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: sugar-free dessert
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on box using skim milk. Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on box.
Add to top of pudding bowls.
Makes 4 servings.
Only 94 calories per serving.

title: self frosted (and yummy)
directions: Mix first three ingredients into saucepan and bring to a boil. Immediately pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place pecans approximately where you would estimate the cake pieces will be cut.
I just chop up the nuts and sprinkle over mixture.
Pour prepared cake mix over the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or test with toothpick for doneness.
Cool.
Cut around outside edge and tip pan upside down on large cake plate.
Cake is frosted.

title: pasta spinach salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
In a bowl, combine pasta, tomatoes, cheese, salad dressing, green onion and olives.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours or overnight for best results.
Sprinkle oregano, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange spinach on serving platter. Spoon pasta over spinach.
Serve.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Place the rice in a 2 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Mix the chicken with salsa, and put this on the rice.
Pour cheese sauce over the chicken mixture.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel apple oat squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, baking soda and salt. Cut in margarine until crumbly. Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
Press remainder on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes. Add nuts to reserved crumb mixture.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Crush the cookies until a 9 x 13-inch pan is covered.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk and spread in pan. Cover this with Cool Whip. Sprinkle a few crumbled cookies on top.

title: mcfarlain's pot roast
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot on stovetop. Cover and cook on low heat for 3 hours or until tender.

title: crab or shrimp spread
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 3 tablespoons cold water.
Add to mushroom soup that has been warmed.
Add cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into molds and refrigerate.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: sausage roll
directions: Peel away casing of sausage and chop meat into small pieces. Brown in skillet sprayed with Pam.
On a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam, pressing with fingers, spread the biscuit dough.
Make sure seams are tightly sealed and there are no holes or thin spots.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Roll up dough to enclose filling.
Bake on middle shelf for 30 minutes or until golden brown in preheated 350° oven.
Check after 15 or 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Add applesauce, milk, brown sugar, oil and egg white. Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups almost full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until deep golden brown.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients, except potato chips. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with mashed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine ingredients; pour over sliced pickles until they are covered.
Keep in refrigerator.
Will last a long time.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for filling together, adding pecans last. Pour
into	pie
shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat
to
and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
When pie is done,
outer edges of filling should be set and center slightly soft.

title: wiggles
directions: Fry bacon in skillet. Lift out and fry hamburger in bacon fat until brown.
Then put in roaster and add all cooked vegetables and spaghetti and mix.
Arrange bacon, then cheese on top.
Pour the tomato paste on top of cheese; put in oven and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
You can also put hot into jars, seal and use later.

title: baked beans and beef dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble the meat.
Drain off excess fat juice and throw away.
Combine cooked beef and all the rest of the ingredients together, except the bacon.

title: baked scalloped corn
directions: Mix well in a baking dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 3/4 hour at 350°.
Take out of oven and let set for 20 minutes to settle before serving. Serves 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve on crackers.
This will keep for a long period of time in refrigerator.

title: taco salad
directions: Pull lettuce apart in small pieces.
Add tomato, onion, beans and cheese.
Add chips, dressing and mayonnaise.
Mix all together.

title: peach delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put Pam in 2 round pans.
Drain peaches, reserving sauce.
Add enough water to reserved sauce to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, except substitute sauce mixture for water and substitute 2 egg whites for 1 egg.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake and cool as directed.
Cut peaches into bite size pieces.
Mix yogurt and whipped topping; fold in peaches.
Fill layers with about half of the peach mixture. Spoon remaining mixture over top of cake.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Delicious and low fat.

title: strawberry and sour cream jello
directions: Mix hot water and jello until jello is dissolved.
Add the strawberries and pineapple and stir well.
Add bananas and stir. Put half of this mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and let it jell.
After it jells, spread the sour cream over the top, then pour in rest of jello mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate to set firm.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage in vegetable oil, drain.
In large fry pan combine all ingredients.
Add chicken stock as needed to keep moist.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove bay leaf prior to serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and instant chocolate mix.
Mix butter and sugar until creamy and add each egg, one at a time and mix well.
Add food coloring and vanilla.
Mix buttermilk, vinegar and soda.
Blend on low speed with an electric mixer, adding flour mixture, creamed butter and sugar mixture and buttermilk mixture alternately and mixing well after each addition.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package, drain and rinse; set aside.
Brown ground beef and sausage, drain off fat.
Add onion and green pepper, cook until tender.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder or salt to taste.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and olives. Mix together well and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: onion rings(low fat recipe)
directions: Cut onions into 1/2 inch rounds and separate rings. Place in a bowl and toss with buttermilk. In another bowl, combine breadcrumbs, salt and pepper. Dredge onion rings in dry mixture and place on lightly oiled baking sheet. Lightly mist with olive oil cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 4 servings.

title: pat-in-pan pie crust
directions: Place the flour, sugar and salt in the pie pan and mix with your fingers until blended.
In a measuring cup, combine the oil and milk and beat with a fork until creamy.
Pour all at once over the flour mixture.
Mix with fork until completely moistened.
Pat the dough with your fingers, first up the sides, then across the bottom; flute the edges.
If a prebaked shell is needed, prick pastry and bake 15 minutes at 425°; checking often and pricking when necessary.
For a 10-inch shell, use 2 cups flour, 2 teaspoon sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, 2/3 cup oil and 3 tablespoons milk.

title: eggplant salad or spread(salata de vinete)
directions: Roast the eggplants whole over an open flame (you can also do this on top of your stove) until the skin is very black, crusty, peeling and eggplant feels soft all over.
Peel off the skin.
Chop into sections and let drain in a colander.
Once drained, chop finely.
You can use an electric mixer to make it a nice, smooth texture.

title: orange bread
directions: Cover rinds with cold water.
Let come to a boil, and then drain.
Repeat twice more.
Boil until tender in the third water, and drain.
Add rinds to 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Boil until syrup is thick.
Drain the syrup into a dish.
Cool and cut peelings into syrup, add 1 beaten egg, 1 teaspoon shortening, 1 cup milk, 3 cups of sifted flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 3 teaspoons of baking powder.
Bake in a loaf pan, 40 minutes at 375°.

title: cinnamon twists(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Heat to lukewarm in a large saucepan the sour cream.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, soda and salt.
Crumble into mixture and stir until dissolved the cake of yeast.
Add egg, shortening and flour.
Mix well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Will make 2 small loaves.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in the 1 cup boiling water.
Add the strawberries. Add the gelatine and pineapple.
Add the chopped nuts.
May add the marshmallows. Add the lemon juice.
Pour in dish and chill overnight.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cool and take off bone.
Save broth.

title: california casserole
directions: In hot margarine, saute onions about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, salt and pepper. Toss lightly to mix well.
Layer half rice mixture in lightly greased baking dish, half the chiles and sprinkle with half the cheese; repeat.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes or until bubbly hot in 375° oven.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Empty blueberries into strainer.
Wash under cold running water.
Set aside to drain.
Pour oil into one 8-inch round pan; tilt pan to cover bottom.
Put muffin mix, egg and water into pan; stir with a fork until blended.
Sprinkle drained blueberries, brown sugar and cinnamon over batter; use fork to fold into batter to create a marbled effect.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes until tests done with a toothpick.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream all ingredients together and use to ice a cooled cake.

title: hot rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream Crisco and sugar; add beaten egg, water, salt and yeast.
Add flour and mix well.
Put in 2 large bowls and grease top of dough.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
When ready to use, take as much dough as needed and shape into rolls.
Put in greased pan.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Let rise for 3 hours and bake at 400° until brown.

title: chocolate candy(who doesn't like chocolates?)
directions: In a bowl, cream together the butter, Eagle Brand milk and powdered sugar.
Add the coconut, nuts and flavoring.
Chill in refrigerator at least an hour, then roll dough into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and chill again.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese thinly over tortillas.
Down center of each tortilla, sprinkle
olives, chiles and salsa.
Roll up and cut into bite size pieces.

title: pizza dip
directions: Place cream cheese in microwave to soften.
Spread cream cheese at the bottom of a tin pan.
Pour in sauce and sprinkle Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Put in oven until cheese bubbles at 350°.
Dip nachos.

title: apple-grape salad(fat burner)
directions: Cut apples crosswise in thin slices.
Arrange grapes, apples and mint leaves in a glass bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar and lemon juice.
Toss lightly, then cover.
Chill one hour before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat all ingredients; pour into greased dish.

title: carrot cornbread
directions: Sift flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture forms little lumps the size of peas.
Beat egg in a small bowl until frothy; stir in buttermilk and carrots.
Pour mixture into dry ingredients; stir until well mixed.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Bake at 425 degrees for 20 minutes or until center springs back when pressed with fingertips.
Cool in pan on wire rack; cut into large squares.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking dish. Mix together the flour and baking powder.
Using a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut the butter into the flour mixture until coarse crumbs form.

title: cheesy spinach bake
directions: Drain spinach, squeezing out excess liquid.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 1 quart dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli pecan salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill overnight or a few hours before serving.

title: lemon icebox cake
directions: Cook lemon pudding according to directions on box.
After pudding has cooled (not completely thickened), mix with Cool Whip.

title: marble cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add the milk and mix well.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan, keeping a small portion of batter in mixing bowl.
Drop 4 to 5 drops of red food coloring into remaining mixture.
Mix well and drop by a spoonful at a time over the mixture in the pan.
(This makes the marble effect.) Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
If desired, frost with favorite frosting.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cook cucumbers in salt water overnight.
Drain for 10 minutes in colander, then mix onions and other stuff.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.

title: lenora's pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Add peppers, onions, water, soup and seasonings.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Serve over mashed potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: hunter-style lamb stew
directions: Spray a large skillet or saucepan with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat.
Add lamb cubes and garlic; cook 5 minutes, or until lamb is evenly browned, stirring frequently.
Add apple juice, 1/2 cup broth, rosemary, pepper and sage; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 hour, or until lamb is tender.

title: creamy coconut cake(pina colada cake)
directions: Bake a white cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While warm, prick entire cake with end of a wooden spoon.
Pour a can of Eagle Brand milk and a can of cream of coconut over cake.
Cool cake.
Top with 1/2 package of coconut, then a small container of Cool Whip, then the remaining coconut.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour melted butter on bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over melted butter.
Sprinkle chopped nuts evenly over crumbs. Scatter chocolate and butterscotch chips over nuts.
Sprinkle coconut evenly over chips. Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over coconut.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Cut into bars.

title: kielbasa delight
directions: Cover bite sized sausage pieces with pineapple, chili sauce and brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours, basting frequently. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: chocolate cream crunch
directions: Crust:
Combine flour, pecans and butter.
Mix well and press into bottom of a 9 x 12-inch cake pan or baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: mom's vegetable soup
directions: Put all the vegetables in a Dutch oven or deep pan.
Cook until all vegetables are done.

title: baked turkey drumsticks
directions: Wrap each drumstick tightly in aluminum foil with the following ingredients:
2 tablespoons onion, 2 tablespoons celery, 2 slices fried bacon and 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Season with salt, pepper and celery salt.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Very tender and juicy.
Can also be baked on outdoor grill.

title: sour cream mustard dressing
directions: Mix together 2 hours before using.
(Keeps well!)

title: egg custard
directions: Melt margarine. Mix sugar and flour. Add margarine.
Add one egg at a time.
Mix well after each.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a greased and lightly floured baking dish. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cheery pie
directions: Cut shortening & salt into flour until pieces are like small peas.
Add water & mix with fork until moist.
Divide dough in half.
Flour the counter & roll out dough with roller.
Put on the bottom of a pie plate.

Do the same for the top of the pie. 2 large cans of cherry pie filling; put in pie shell; add 1 Tbsp of butter on the top of the filling; make air vents in the top & bake at 400 for 45 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.

title: white salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
To juice, add 1 cup sugar and boil for 5 minutes.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in 6 tablespoons water.
Add to juice.
When juice is cool but not cold, add 8 ounces cream cheese that was mixed with pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.

title: willie muffs
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add cream and mix.
Cook in miniature muffin tins.
Cook in oven at 425° for 12 minutes or until brown.
These are really neat!

title: refrigerator pan rolls
directions: Mix together with mixer hot water, sugar, salt and margarine. Add yeast dissolved in warm water.
Add well beaten egg and 2 3/4 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add by hand 2 1/2 cups flour. Knead until smooth and elastic.
Put in greased bowl, turning in order that all might be covered.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and make rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
May be refrigerated for 4 or 5 days.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and celery until tender.
Add to cooked chicken. Add olives, tomatoes and 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix and add to cooked spaghetti.
Mix well.
Put in deep baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(If you use the broth that is remaining after boiling chicken to cook your spaghetti in, it will have more flavor.)

title: everything chowder
directions: In medium saucepan, saute bacon and onion until golden brown. Add potatoes and 3/4 cup water; bring to a boil.
Cover boil gently about 10 minutes tender, not mushy.
Add corn, milk, butter, salt, pepper, sugar and veggies; simmer covered until veggies tender but not soft.

title: flounder florentine pinwheels
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix in Ricotta cheese, sauteed onion, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, Cavender's and bread crumbs. Season fillets with salt and pepper.
Place spinach mixture on fillet, about 1/2-inch thick.
Roll up fillet, small end to large and secure with toothpicks.
Place in baking dish.
Pour stock over and sprinkle with a few more bread crumbs.
Top with melted butter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes until fish flakes.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: In small bowl mix flour with shredded zucchini, pepper, salt and egg yolks.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, then add to mixture.
Drop by tablespoon into a skillet in hot oil. Brown on both sides.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook chicken and cut into bite sized pieces.
In a saucepan heat soup, sour cream, onion and chilies for five minutes.
On tortilla, place some chicken and 2 tablespoons of soup mix.
Continue for all tortillas.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.
May need to layer tortillas.
If so, put some soup mix over the bottom layer.
Do this to the top layer, also.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix cream cheese and onions.
Dissolve cubes in hot water and mix in cream cheese mixture.
May add a little milk if too thick. Stuff celery.

title: after dinner mints
directions: Beat egg white with water until fluffy.
Mix in powdered sugar and butter and make a round ball.
Divide into three parts and add mint flavoring or color of your choice.
Pinch off small amount about the size of a dime.
Roll into a ball; lay on waxed paper. When they dry a little, mash with a table fork to make an indentation.
Let dry overnight.
This will make about 100 mints.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: In large kettle, put stew beef, turnip and onion.
Boil on medium heat until turnip is tender.
Add carrots and potatoes. Cook until carrots and potatoes are done.

title: beef stroganoff 1
directions: Pound the round steak, then cut into cubes.
Flour lightly and brown in oil with garlic clove.
Shake paprika over each side as cooked.
Slice the onions and brown with the meat.
Mix the vegetable stock or bouillon with the meat sauce, seasonings and spices.
Pour over meat and onions.
Sprinkle all with more paprika.
Simmer for about 1 1/2 hours; when ready to serve, mix in the horseradish and the sour cream and simmer for a few more minutes.

title: spicy apple muffins
directions: Prepare apples.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of sugar.
Let stand while preparing batter.
Spoon flour (not sifted) into dry measuring cup.
Level off and pour measured flour into bowl.
Add 1/4 cup of sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon to flour (not sifted).
Stir well.
Combine milk, shortening and egg in small bowl.
Beat slightly.
Add sugared apples; mix well.
Add liquid ingredients all at once to dry.
Stir until moistened.
Fill lined or well-greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen muffins.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar and spices.
Add beaten egg, milk, vanilla and oil to dry mix.
Stir until mixed well.
Add blueberries last and pour into muffin pans.
I spray my muffin pan with Pam and bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: crisp cereal pie crust
directions: Mix and press in greased 9-inch
pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool before filling.

title: cheese-potato fluff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook potatoes until tender; drain and mash potatoes.
Add butter, cheese and milk.
Heat over low heat until butter and cheese melts.
Fold in eggs.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except for pecans, and form into a ball.
Roll ball in pecans and chill overnight before serving.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Cook pie crust and let cool.
Mix Jell-O by directions. Chill, but do not let it start to get thick.
Blend the ice cream in with the Jell-O and then the strawberries.
Pour in pie crust and put in refrigerator.
Makes two pies.

title: gingered fruit dip
directions: Whip the first 4 ingredients together.
Serve in a bowl on a tray surrounded with fresh fruit and toothpicks.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephants into bite sized pieces. This should take about 2 months.

Add enough gravy to cover. Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 465°. This will serve 2,800 people. If more are expected, the 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew. This is obviously a family favorite!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir together the flour, soda and salt.
In a mixer bowl, beat butter and shortening on medium speed of electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.

title: mexican pie
directions: Warm beans; drain and mash.
Layer bottom of 9 x 11-inch rectangular dish with beans.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream, then pour over beans.
Add layer of salsa, then layer mild Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over entire dish.
Sprinkle onions to garnish and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream cheese and margarine very soft.
Blend the cream cheese and butter with a spoon.
Add sugar, a little at a time, still using spoon to blend. Add eggs, one at a time, using mixer to blend.
Add vanilla after eggs, using mixer.

title: julie's shrimp dip
directions: Mix soup and cream cheese in blender.
Add shrimp.
Chill and serve.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir meat, onions and green pepper until all is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Heat well. Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper, milk, beaten eggs, butter, onion, cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: baked creamy grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bring 2 c. milk and chicken broth to a boil.
Add grits in a thin stream; cook over low heat for 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add butter, salt and remaining 1/2 c. milk. Beat well and mix in eggs.
Pour into prepared dish and bake for 50-55 minutes.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Spread cheese mixture into an ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: bun bars (candy)(yields 60 bars)
directions: Melt chocolate chips with peanut butter in saucepan, stirring until smooth.
Stir in peanuts.
Spread half of the mixture in greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Let stand until cool.

title: quick chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken (microwave), then cut in small pieces.
Simmer onion until "clear."
Add onion and chilies to soup.
Soften tortillas by turning in hot oil for a few seconds.
Put some chicken, a little of soup mixture and cheese on tortilla.
Roll up, etc.
Put remaining cheese and soup on top of all rolled enchiladas.
Heat through in microwave.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water and cook until tender.
Add milk and spices and simmer.
About 30 minutes before you want to serve the soup, add the stick of butter.
I sprinkle shredded cheese on top.

title: sherried chicken
directions: Light oven.
Grease pan.
Crack nuts.
Get out bowl, spoons, ingredients.
Remove 18 blocks and 7 toy cars from kitchen. Measure 2 cups flour onto piece of wax paper.
Get sifter out of cabinet.
Remove Johnny's hands from flour.
Wash flour off of him.

title: cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into cupcake paper cups in pan. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: homemade soup
directions: Clean cabbage, onions and potatoes; cut up into bite-size pieces.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Great with fried cornbread.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chocolate creams
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat, or microwave.
Remove from heat. Add confectioners sugar, egg and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Chill until firm enough to handle, about 30 minutes.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in decorations.
Pecan halves may be pressed into tops instead of rolling in chopped almonds.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse kidney beans.
Combine all ingredients.
Add just enough salad dressing to moisten.
Chill 6 hours to overnight.

title: deviled swiss steak
directions: Mix dry mustard and flour.
Pound into steak.
Brown in fat in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until steak is tender.

title: lemon pie
directions: Stir Cool Whip, lemonade and condensed milk together until smooth.
Pour into crusts.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 2 pies.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Mix the bananas and eggs together in large bowl.
Stir in the flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Add the walnuts and blend.

title: eggs taos
directions: Saute garlic and onion in butter on high heat.
Stir in flour. Add heated milk and whisk until thick.
Add chilies, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Scramble eggs in skillet and set aside.
Mash avocados in small bowl.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of sauce, 1/8 of eggs and 1/8 of avocado on tortilla.
Roll and place seam side down in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over tortillas, sprinkle with cheese and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with sour cream and chopped tomato.

title: classic red kidney beans and rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add ham, onion, pepper and garlic.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Serve over hot white rice.

title: gourmet souffle
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place 6 slices of bread, buttered face down in pan, crusts removed.
Add ham, mushrooms, green pepper, green onions and Cheddar and Jack cheeses.
Cover with 6 slices of bread that has been cubed.
It is easier to cube when slightly frozen.
Add eggs, beaten with milk. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, on cookie sheet at 350° for 1 hour until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine egg, bread crumbs, tomato juice and onions.
Add ground beef and shape into patties.
Brown in skillet.
Add gravy mix and water, stirring until smooth.
Cover and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add eggs, butter, extracts and nuts.
Put small amount of batter (1/2 to 1 teaspoon) on cookie sheet lined with foil.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool, then peel off foil.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken, skin side down, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with pineapple spears.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.
Turn chicken once while baking.

title: quick and easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Mix ingredients as listed.
Pour batter into buttered pan.
Pour peaches and juice over batter.
Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake until brown on top at 350° (approximately 50 minutes).

title: taylor's macaroni
directions: Cook noodles until done; drain.
Mix milk and egg.
In the bottom of a 3-quart casserole dish, put 1/2 noodles.
Then pour 1/2 egg and milk over noodles.
Then 1/2 Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Lay 6 slices American and 3 slices Swiss cheese next. Then sprinkle with Parmesan and Romano cheese.
Then repeat all layers.
Makes 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
(Add salt and butter on top of layer before cooking.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Boil and whip sweet potatoes ahead or use canned potatoes. Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add water to dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Gradually add to sugar mixture.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Fold in nuts and raisins.

title: sour cream twists
directions: Measure the warm water into mixing bowl; add yeast, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board and fold over several times until smooth. Roll into an oblong (24 x 6-inch).
Spread with 2 tablespoons of softened butter.
Sprinkle half of dough with a mixture of 1/3 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Fold other half over. Cut into 24 strips 1 inch wide.
Hold strip at both ends and twist in opposite directions.
Place on greased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Press both ends of twist to baking sheet.
Cover and let rise until doubled (1 hour).
Bake until golden brown at 375° (12 to 15 minutes).
While warm, frost with icing.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cook until done.
Cream the cream cheese and sour cream.
Add hot drained potatoes.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: greek salad
directions: Mix broccoli and cauliflower, olives and dressing in a bowl; refrigerate overnight.
Drain off excess oil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Can also sprinkle bacon bits on top.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Add each ingredient in order.
Cover with mayonnaise and let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Mix and serve.

title: charlie cake
directions: Beat all but the last two ingredients in a large bowl.
Fold in butterscotch chips and coconut.
Pour into Bundt pan that has been well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes (some ovens may vary).
Remove immediately from pan.
Cool on rack.
No frosting or glaze is necessary.
A very moist cake.

title: sweet potato pancakes
directions: In a food processor (steel shredding blade), shred 1 very large sweet potato to make 3 cups.
Transfer potatoes to a bowl and add beaten eggs, grated onion, flour, baking powder and salt.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into a greased pan.
Add all wet ingredients.
Stir with fork until blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with frosting.

title: oatmeal banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the flour, oats, baking powder, salt and soda.
Set aside.
In a small mixer bowl, beat eggs. Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle more cheese on top and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: morman bread(keeps longer)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add first 4 cups of flour and stir. Add shortening, sugar and salt, then stir.
Add additional flour and knead until it springs back.
Cover and let rise to double in bulk.
Then punch down, put in loaf pans and let rise again.
Then bake at 350° until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft, but not browned.
Add rice and stir over moderate heat 3 or 4 minutes, until rice grains appear white and opaque.
Add broth, water, salt, seasonings, celery and tomato.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and turn heat to low and cook 15 minutes.
Add peas and shrimp.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Cook until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed. Makes 5 servings.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl cream shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Add flour, salt, baking powder and mix until blended.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Press each ball around a candy kiss, completely enclosing the kiss (like a chocolate covered cherry). Bake 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Chop the shrimp coarsely.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and catsup.
Mix with shrimp, celery and eggs.
Chill and serve on crisp lettuce.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fast brown chops and remove from skillet.
Drain off excess oil.
Pan boil rice (do not overcook).
Put rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with tomatoes, garlic, parsley and oil. Place pork chops on top.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender and chops are tender, then bake for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: debbie's country fried chicken
directions: Take chicken and dip in the buttermilk.
Place in the flour and roll until meat is covered all over.
Place in hot vegetable oil and cook slowly.

title: lo-cal vegetable stew
directions: Place tomatoes in saucepan; break up.
Add vegetables, except beans.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Add beans.
Stir and heat well. Serve with French bread or corn bread and forget the calories! Can be refrigerated and reheated.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Blend together.
Keeps several weeks in refrigerator.

title: aunt della's nine day sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cut into chunks.
Mix salt and water in given proportions enough to cover cucumbers; heat and pour over cucumbers, which have been packed in a stone jar.
Let stand 3 days.
Drain and discard brine.
Make a solution of 3 tablespoons alum to 1 gallon water; heat and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 3 days.
Drain.
Cover with clear water and let stand overnight. Drain for 30 minutes.
Replace in stone jar.
Make solution of 1/2 gallon vinegar (white) and 4 quarts sugar.
Tie 1/2 box pickling spices in a cloth and place down in jar.
Let stand 3 days. Remove from stone jar and pack in canning jars.
Heat vinegar solution to boiling.
Cover pickles and seal.

title: double trick cheese bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add soup and dressing mix.
Slowly add flour to form stiff dough.
Knead about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, cover, let rise until double, about 30 minutes. Shape dough into 4 (10-inch) loaves.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover; let rise until light and double, about 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool immediately on wire racks.

title: hamburger-macaroni casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil; drain.
Add other ingredients, except macaroni.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add macaroni; cook on low heat for 40 minutes, stirring often so macaroni doesn't stick.
If you need more sauce, use tomato juice.
Top with grated cheese or Parmesan before serving.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 11 x 7-inch casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately with nacho chips.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and pineapple; mix well.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Coat chops in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown chops in skillet.
Place chops in baking dish.
Combine soup, water, ginger and rosemary; pour over chops.
Sprinkle with half of the onion rings.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with remaining onion rings and continue baking 10 minutes.
Remove meat to platter.
Blend sour cream into soup mixture; heat through.
Serve meat and gravy with fluffy rice.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys and you will have a good cake.
Proverbs 13:24.

title: low calorie casserole
directions: Cut cabbage in small pieces and put in bottom of greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onion.
Pour off fat and stir in rice.
Put mixture on top of cabbage and cover all with tomato soup and water mixed.
Bake at 350° For 1 hour.

title: ham potato cheese casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until just tender.
Layer ham in 3-quart baking dish.
Layer potatoes, then cheese.
Mix mashed potatoes with hot water.
Make the potatoes very thin.
Add margarine and milk. Pour over potatoes and ham. Stir and bake 3 minutes.

title: macaroni-sausage casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in 3 quarts boiling salted water for 7 to 8 minutes.
Drain well.
Brown sausage; remove and reserve 1/2 sausage.
Saute onion and green peppers in 2 tablespoons fat. Stir in flour and salt.
Slowly add milk.
Cook over medium heat; stir until thick.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Combine macaroni and sauce; turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese and reserved sausage.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes, or until golden.
Serves 6.

title: fresh asparagus pasta
directions: Cut asparagus and onions into 1-inch diagonal pieces.
Cut tomatoes lengthwise in eighths.
Mix 1/2 cup of the chicken broth and the wine together; set aside.
Mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup chicken broth together; set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Combine sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs.
Beat until fluffy. Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture, alternating with water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pans 10 minutes, then turn out.
May add nuts and raisins to recipe.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in bacon grease until translucent.
Add water, salt, pepper and marjoram.
Bring to slow boil.
Add cubed potato. Bring temperature back to slow boil.
Cook potato slowly.
Add corn and milk.
Add bacon bits before serving.

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let cool while combining banana, pineapple, strawberries and pecans.
Add fruit mixture to Jell-O; pour 1/2 mixture into 13 x 9 pan and let set in refrigerator several minutes.
Spread sour cream on partially set Jell-O and top with remaining mixture.
Return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chicken delight
directions: Open dinner rolls.
Spread on chicken. Roll back up and place in casserole
dish.
Mix
soups
and milk together. Pour over rolls.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coo-coo
directions: You will need 1 large round frying pan about 8 to 9-inches.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, shortening and salt.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Dissolve yeast in 2 to 3 tablespoons warm water.
Let it bubble to ensure it is working.
Add to milk mixture along with 2 cups of flour.
Stir and keep adding flour to make a dough that can be handled easily.
Knead for 5 to 8 minutes, then cut into pieces to fill pans 1/2 full.
Be sure to grease pans.
Let rise to twice its size in warm place.
Bake in 400° oven for 35 to 45 minutes to a good golden brown.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Cut flank steak into serving pieces; marinate in fridge overnight or 1 day, turning meat over occasionally.
Broil or grill to desired doneness.

title: barbecue muffins
directions: Separate into 10 biscuits; flatten to 5-inch circles. Press each into bottom and up sides of a greased muffin cup; set aside.

title: peanut butter bar cookies
directions: Bring Karo syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add cornflakes.
Press into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; add tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes, onion, pepper and spices; simmer 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles.
Drain and cover with cold water.
Fill casserole pan (13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 2 3/4-inch) with alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, sauce, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese on top is bubbling (approximately 30 minutes).

title: special ham sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients except buns.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to use.
Fill buns.
Wrap each sandwich in aluminum foil. Bake at 250° to 300° for 30 minutes.

title: mama's mudslide cake
directions: Mix sugar, pecans, flour and margarine. Mix well. Press firmly into
baking dish and bake for 15 minutes at 350°, then mix together 1 cup Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese. Mix well
and
spread
over
baked
layer, then mix real well together the vanilla, the chocolate pudding and cold milk and spread it over the other layers.
Spread the rest of the Cool Whip
on
top, then sprinkle grated Hershey candy bar on top. Place in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours before eating.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Put cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Bake 20 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Whip cream cheese, slowly add milk and pudding mix.
Put on cool cake. Sprinkle with pineapple.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: date logs
directions: Cook until thick the first 4 ingredients.
Add nuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Shape into log.
Put on wax paper and roll in coconut.

title: key lime cake
directions: Combine oil, orange juice, eggs and jello with cake mix, beating until smooth.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let layers cool completely. Combine lime juice and 4x sugar; mix until smooth.
Prick cake layers with fork; drizzle lime sugar mixture over each layer.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in salad oil in heavy pan.
Add water.
Add remaining ingredients (except tomato juice).
Cover and simmer over low heat for about 2 hours, stirring frequently.
If additional liquid is needed, add tomato juice.
Serve hot with crackers. Yield:
15 to 18 servings.

title: condensed milk
directions: Combine and mix with mixer or blender.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Will keep for some time.

title: the prize winning pie
directions: Finely crush the graham crackers for the crust.
Add sugar and melted oleo.
Shape into pie plate.
Put the strawberry glaze into the crust; clean and cut strawberries and add to the glaze. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Chill and serve.
Cut a couple of strawberries and place on top of Cool Whip for looks.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding using cold milk.
When thickened, fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
On top of that, put 1/2 of pudding/Cool Whip mixture.
Add a second layer of graham crackers.
Then add the last half of pudding mixture. Add third layer of graham crackers.
Carefully frost with chocolate icing.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Starter should be kept in glass jar with metal lid, large enough to hold 3 cups.
Punch 6 or 8 holes in lid so starter can breath.
Leave out on counter for 8 to 12 hours.
Use one cup to make bread; refrigerate balance and in 3 to 5 days, feed starter. The day you put it in the refrigerator is day one.
You must remove 1 cup of starter when you feed.
This can be used to make bread or give to a friend.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving one cup of the juice (if not enough, add mandarin orange juice).
Mix reserved juice and pudding mix in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Cook uncovered on High for 3 minutes or until thick and clear.
Or if you are not using microwave, cook pudding.
Stir pudding mix into reserved juice from pineapple and oranges.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Stir in drained oranges and pineapple chunks.
Chill.
Add cherries and bananas when ready to serve.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to sauerkraut and mix.
Chill covered for several hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup French fried onions. Pour mixed beans in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Put the last 1/2 cup French fried onions on top and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes more or until onions are golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Chop peppers very fine with
blender or food processor. If using blender, add vinegar	to
peppers.
Combine
peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 10 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cook egg yolks, sugar and vinegar.
Cool.
Add pineapple, cherries, almonds and marshmallows.
Add whipped cream to fruit mixture.
Beat egg whites, fold in and freeze.

title: oatmeal cake with frosting
directions: Put oats in a mixing bowl and pour boiling water over oats. Set aside for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and stem berries; set aside 1/2 of the best berries. Crush well the remaining 1/2 berries and bring to a boil in heavy saucepan.
Blend sugar and cornstarch; add to boiling berries and cook until thick.
Cool slightly and pour over the raw berries that have been placed in baked pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: pig stomach
directions: Mix onion, potatoes, parsley, pepper and salt.
Cut into pieces the smoked sausage and pork.
Stuff pig stomach with ingredients and close by needle and thread.
Place filled stomach in roasting pan; add water in bottom.
Bake at 350°
for ??? hours until tender.
Remove from roaster and add browned butter.
Serve with broth.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla. Whip cream and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spread into 9-inch pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift the flour with cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt and combine with sugar.
In another bowl, mix egg, milk and oil, then add it to flour mixture.
Add chopped apples.
Put paper baking cups in muffin pan.
Fill half full with batter.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.
Test with toothpick.

title: salsa
directions: Dice tomatoes, onions, peppers and chilies; season to taste. Chill and serve. This can be adjusted for mildness, depending on the type of peppers you use. Be creative. Use yellow, orange and red banana peppers.
Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Combine cottage cheese with next 4 ingredients.
Layer in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan 1/2 noodles, 1/2 cottage cheese mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: sesame topped "koulourakia" - easter cookies
directions: Combine butter, oil and sugar; beat until light and fluffy. Add 3 eggs, orange juice and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Sift flour with baking powder (add 3 cups flour with baking powder). Add to butter mixture and mix well.
Knead in remaining flour to make a medium dough.
Shape as desired.

title: pineapple topping for cheesecake
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan (medium size) and cook over medium heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly until mixture clears.
Let cool a little and spread over warm cheesecake.

title: decorator's icing
directions: Sift and weigh sugar; set aside.
Cream together remaining ingredients with mixer.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Mix until well blended.
Add food coloring as desired.
Yield:
1 cake.

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix at slow speed the flour, sugar, mayonnaise, milk, eggs, soda, salt and spices.
Mix for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Frost with Dream Whip.

title: banana creme pie
directions: Scald 1 3/4 cups milk with Karo.
Mix remaining ingredients except vanilla and add quickly to milk and Karo combination.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Use meringue or Dream Whip for topping.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon and put into large bowl.
Add crushed crackers, finely chopped onion and egg.
Mix well.
Add flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper; mix together.
Pat into patties about 1 inch in diameter and 1/2 inch thick.
Cook in hot oil until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: chicken breasts in orange sauce
directions: Wash
chicken
and
arrange
on greased baking pan.
In double boiler,
put egg yolks, sugar, all the juice, peel and melted butter.
Cook over hot water for about 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken
and
bake	at
400° for 1 hour or until tender. Serve each chicken breast with a slice of orange as a garnish, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Toast pecans in 1/4 cup butter in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan in a 350° oven about 15 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from oven; cool thoroughly.
Set aside, reserving 2/3 cup pecans for frosting.
Combine flour, baking powder, and salt.
Set aside. Beat 1 cup butter, gradually adding 2 cups sugar, beating well. Add eggs beating well after each.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat well. Stir in vanilla and 1 1/3 cups toasted pecans.
Put in 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake on 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Cool layers completely.
For frosting beat 1/4 cup butter until fluffy.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla, and enough milk to make frosting of good spreading consistency.
Stir in reserved toasted pecans.
Spread frosting between layers, on top and sides.

title: baked grits
directions: Mix
together
grits,
eggs,
butter and enough milk to make mixture
soupy.
Bake
at 350° for about 45 minutes until brown. After baked can be warmed up in the microwave.

title: cinnamon flan(spanish)
directions: Combine sugar and 2 teaspoons water in heavy small skillet. Cook, stirring constantly, until caramelized and syrup. Immediately pour into warm 4-cup buttered mold.
Tilt to coat bottom and sides of container while sugar is still hot.
Beat eggs well.
Add milk, 1 cup water, cinnamon and lemon peel.
Mix well. Pour into prepared mold.
Place casserole in longer pan containing hot water to level of custard.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool completely. Loosen custard with knife.
Put on serving platter and spoon caramel over top.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Preparation time: 1 hour.

title: english toffee
directions: Lightly butter an 11 x 15-inch sheet.
Combine butter and sugar in a 4-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, beating hard until mixture boils.
Cover with tight lid; cook 3 minutes. Remove lid and stir occasionally until it reaches 290° on a candy thermometer.
Add about 1/4 cup of the toasted almonds.
Pour into a buttered pan; set on flat surface to cool 30 minutes. Refrigerate 15 minutes while chocolate melts (either over boiling water in double boiler or in microwave oven).

title: 24 hour pickles
directions: Put
water,
vinegar
and salt in 1/2 gallon jar.
Peel cucumbers
and
slice
them 1/4-inch thick.
Slice onion.
Put cucumbers,
onion and dill in jar.
Set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
It's ready to eat and lasts for many days.

title: granny wedding cookies
directions: Mix ingredients with hands.
Shape into balls about the size of acorns.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Let cool about 5 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
These are good appetizers for any kind of celebration.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, eggs, flour and sugar in small, deep dish casserole.
Top with cubed bread soaked in butter.
Bake approximately 35 minutes at 350°.

title: unstuffed cabbage(tastes just like the labor-intensive old favorite)
directions: Crumble beef into Dutch oven.
Add onions and cook over medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring until beef is lightly browned.

title: sweet-sour green beans
directions: Cut off tips of beans; leave whole.
Separate onions into rings.
Cook beans in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Combine beans and onion rings in a large bowl.
Stir the remaining ingredients together.
Pour over beans.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts (14 cups).

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Drain.
Combine soup, milk, water and cheese in 3 qt. saucepan.
Cook, stir over medium heat until cheese melts and sauce is hot.
Stir in noodles, turkey, peas, carrots, and pimentos.
Spoon into greased baking dish.
Combine crumbs, parmesan and parsley.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6.

title: crawfish quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms and green onions in butter until tender.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine eggs, half and half, salt, dry mustard and cheese.
Fold in crawfish, mushrooms and onions.
Pour mixture into shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and continue to bake for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Blend until moistened.
Beat on medium for two minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish, layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 tuna, 1/2 soup, 1/2 broccoli, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 croutons.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour into square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Place orange and lemon juice in 1 cup measure.
Fill with other fruit juice.
Add sugar.
Beat egg yolks and flour.
Add to ingredients.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Pour over stiffly beaten egg whites.
When cool, add cream (whipped).
Serves 12.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soups (rinse cans with water and add this to mix), vegetables and cheese. Pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan or dish. Mix biscuit mix, egg and milk, adding a few parsley flakes. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: creamy chicken broccoli
directions: In skillet, cook chicken and dressing about
8 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt and melted butter.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Slowly add coconut and flavorings.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake at 375° until firm.
Watch carefully if pie browns before fillings sets, you may lower temperature to 350° for the last minutes of baking.

title: "bakeless" ziti
directions: Cook ziti according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, combine sauce and pepper flakes in a medium sized saucepan; heat through. Combine ziti, sauce mixture, Ricotta and Mozzarella in a large serving bowl. Sprinkle with Parmesan. Makes 6 servings. Preparation time: 3 minutes. Cook time: 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix ingredients and simmer for approximately 2 hours.

title: barbecue rice
directions: Smother onions and celery in skillet with 1 stick oleo.
Add liquid smoke, salt, pepper and all soups. Add 4 cups cooked rice and bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: french toast
directions: Slice French bread into thick slices into a baking dish.
Pour mixture over bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add blueberries, if wanted.

title: noodles divine
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook onion and carrot in butter or margarine over medium heat for 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, water and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in noodles.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Add broccoli and cook 10 minutes more or until broccoli and noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Makes 8 side-dish servings.

title: perfect no bake cheesecake
directions: In blender, sprinkle gelatine over cold milk; let stand 2 minutes.
Add hot milk; blend all until well mixed.
Add cream cheese that has been softened; beat until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix well.
In microwave, melt chocolate chips; spread over crust.
Pour filling over.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Decorate top with grated nuts, chips or whipped topping.
Serves 10.
Light and delicious!

title: play dough(not to be eaten)
directions: Boil water and salt. Remove from heat. Add cooking oil, alum and food coloring.
Quickly mix in the flour and knead.
Knead while it is still hot.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake into small pieces and place in a large deep bowl. Mix sour cream, milk, whipped topping and sugar until smooth. Fold into cake.
Mix glaze with strawberries and top the large bowl of cake mixture.
Chill several hours before serving.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.
The strawberries and glaze mixture seals the cake mixture in the bottom of bowl.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until lemon colored.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. Add vanilla; remove from heat.
Add chips and stir.
Grease large cookie sheet or jelly roll pan; line with wax paper.
Pour fudge into pan and chill until firm.

title: rancher's dinner
directions: Lightly brown sausages and set aside.
Prepare Kraft dinner as directed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and place in buttered casserole. Top with browned sausages.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: tender pie crust
directions: In deep bowl, work boiling water into shortening with whisk or fork until all water is absorbed and shortening is light and fluffy like batter.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Mix in a pinch of salt.
If necessary, add tiny amount of water to achieve correct texture.
Roll out into 2 crusts (or roll out 1 crust and keep the other half of dough in covered bowl for up to 1 week.)

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Mix oil and sugar in a small bowl.
Mash the bananas.
Mix bananas with sugar and oil. Add flour and nuts which have been dusted with a teaspoon of flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Bake in cupcake pans.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
(Optional:
crumble potato chips on top of casserole.) Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 1 hour.

title: mint swirl brownies
directions: Cream together cheese, margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs. Stir together flour, powder and salt.
Stir into cream mixture. Spoon half of batter into another bowl; stir in nuts and chocolate.
Drop chocolate batter from tablespoon, checker board fashion, into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix Treet (diced fine with a fork), cream cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add mayonnaise to your taste. Refrigerate at least 2 hours for flavors to enhance each other.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Cauliflower, broccoli, green onions, carrots and canned sliced mushrooms, drained (cut vegetables fine).

title: sweet mouthful
directions: Mix egg whites, cream of tartar and salt; beat until stiff. Gradually add sugar.
On wax paper, make 3 circles, 8 inches in diameter, with the egg whites.
Place these on a greased cookie sheet(s).
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 250°.
Melt chocolate chips.
Spread thinly over egg white mixture.
Add 3/4 inch whipped cream on each circle.
Add strawberries on top. Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pie filling.
Beat with whisk 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Blend pumpkin, almonds and 2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 4 hours.
Put cream on top.

title: filet of fish in almond butter(a microwave entree)
directions: *I like to use tilapia or orange roughy.

title: broccoli for kids
directions: Cut up broccoli and steam for 5 minutes.
Mix chunky peanut butter and butter; melt on stove or in microwave until hot.
Pour peanut butter sauce over broccoli and serve.
Adjust amount of sauce as needed.

title: red satin punch(good for christmas)
directions: Mix into punch bowl.
Add ice.
Makes about 30 punch cup servings.

title: champagne punch
directions: Thaw juice and lemonade concentrate.
Stir together undiluted concentrates in punch bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring gently.
Serve immediately.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Mix pineapple and marshmallows and set aside.
Cook until thick the mustard, juice, flour and egg yolks.
Add lemon juice and cool.
Combine with reserved fruit mixture and whipped cream. Chill.
Chopped nuts and maraschino cherries may be placed on top.

title: ratatouille nicoise
directions: Saute lightly the eggplant for 2 minutes in 2 tablespoons olive oil and remove eggplant.
Saute the zucchini for 3 to 5 minutes in 2 tablespoons olive oil and remove zucchini.

Saute onions, peppers and garlic for 5 minutes in 2 tablespoons olive oil. Combine all vegetables in alternate layers with tomatoes in casserole dish. Add 1/2 teaspoon basil, salt and pepper to taste. Cover and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Remove cover and bake another 15 minutes or until most of the juice is absorbed.

title: dandy candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until brown; stir constantly (about 10 minutes).
Pour in shallow pan and put 6 chocolate bars on top until soft.
Cover with chopped nuts and put in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour in 2 bread pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheesy beef-stuffed shells
directions: Combine water and salt in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni shells, cook 15 to 18 minutes or just until tender; drain and set aside.
Cook ground beef, onion and garlic in a large skillet until beef is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain off pan drippings and stir in the next 5 ingredients and set aside.
Combine spaghetti sauce and Burgundy; spoon 1/4 of sauce into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside remaining sauce.
Stuff macaroni shells with beef mixture and arrange in baking dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over shells. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sensation salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a quart jar.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, stir well.
For 4 servings, spoon about 3 tablespoons over head of washed, torn and crisped lettuce with plenty of fresh parsley sprinkled on top.
Toss lightly but thoroughly enough to coat.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Tear 1/2 cake into bite size pieces and place in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Mix melted margarine, egg yolks and sugar in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until egg yolks are cooked.
When cool, fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half of mixture over cake pieces.
Crumble 3 candy bars over cake.
Add remainder of cake, broken in pieces.
Pour on remainder of egg mixture.
Cover with last 3 candy bars, crumbled. Refrigerate.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix cheese; roll puffs in butter, then cheese.
Bake in a 450° oven until browned.
Serve hot.

title: meat pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients for 1 hour slow, then add the next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Then spoon into 2 crusts, then put top crust on.
Put a little milk on top of crust and bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes, then at 350° until golden brown, about 30 minutes (put slits in top crust).
Each pie serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil in large bowl.
Add zucchini.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, raisins and nuts.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Add pineapple and pecans and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Cook sugar, eggs and fruit juices until thick.
Cool, then refrigerate.
When cold, add whipped cream.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: barbecue sauce by grandma carrie currin
directions: Mix together all ingredients and let come to boil.
Remove from heat.

title: prawdziwy pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice.
Place in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let stand 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Return to jar and refrigerate.

title: pecan pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the wet ingredients separately.
Add dry ingredients. Pour into 3 (1-pound) coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date nut balls
directions: In food grinder, grind together dates, raisins, apricots and prunes/figs.
Combine with orange juice in 2-quart mixing bowl. Roll into bite-size balls.
Roll in coconut or in nuts. Refrigerate, covered, until time to serve.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, dates and eggs and cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat; add them.
Roll into balls, then into confectioners sugar or coconut or ground nuts.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts (salted to taste) until done.
In a large bowl, combine all soups.
Stir well to combine.
In a large casserole dish, layer about half of the soup mixture, then add a layer of chicken (chopped or pulled apart).
Push chicken down into the soup mixture, then add a layer of chopped broccoli, then a layer of the remaining chicken and finally the remainder of the soup mixture.
Cover the top with corn bread dressing mix.
Place in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: italian sausage
directions: Mix well and use casings and stuff with the meat.
This can be broken down.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Mix together butter, eggs, vanilla and sugar. Add strawberry puree.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened. Spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 24 large muffins.

title: strawberries(candy)
directions: Mix milk and Jell-O, then other ingredients.
Shape like strawberries and roll in red sugar crystals.
Top each with green sugar crystals.
Chill in refrigerator.
Will keep well out of refrigerator.

title: manicotti
directions: Spray 9 x 9-inch glass pan with Pam.
Thin spaghetti sauce with 1/2 to 3/4 cup water.
Spoon 3/4 cup sauce over bottom of pan.
Mix eggs, cheeses, oleo, salt, pepper and basil in a bowl. Use an iced tea spoon to stuff shells.
Lay shells, side by side, in pan.
Spoon over remaining sauce.
Pour another 1/4 cup to 1/2 cup water over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Serve with a green salad and hot bread.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Place in saucepan sugar, flour, cornstarch and cocoa.
Mix and add egg yolks and whole egg.
Stir until mixed.
Add Pet milk, milk, oleo and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Pour in baked crust and cover with meringue browned.

title: buttermilk-raisin biscuits
directions: Soak raisins in applejack 4 to 8 hours; drain, discarding applejack and set aside.
Combine flour and sugar in a large bowl; cut in shortening with a fork or pastry blender until shortening is the size of peas.
Add milk, stirring with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
(Dough will resemble cottage cheese and be sticky.)
Turn dough out onto a heavily floured surface. Add raisins.
Knead lightly 10 to 12 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch round cutter.
Bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes on an ungreased baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except butter and cornflakes. Put into baking dish; sprinkle cornflakes on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix salt, flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat up until frothy.
Add banana.
Fold into flour mixture.
In greased loaf pan, bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: mixed vegetable pilaf
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook mushrooms and basil 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add broth and water; heat to boiling.
Stir in rice; return to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in zucchini and carrot.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand covered 5 minutes before serving.
Makes about 5 cups or 6 servings.

title: meatballs in sauce
directions: Brown meatballs in oven. Mix other ingredients and bring to boil. Add meatballs and simmer.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Take tops off berries and stand berries on heads.
Combine water, sugar, jello and cornstarch and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook until mixture has thickened, pink clear color. Refrigerate until cooled, not not jelled.
Mix strawberries and jello mixture together.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.
Put Cool Whip on top before serving if desired.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Marinate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: brad's brown soup
directions: Brown Cream of Wheat cereal in a large skillet (no oil) on medium heat, stirring with a spatula as needed.
Do not burn!

title: sausage rolls
directions: Have at room temperature.
Add a little water if necessary. Mix all ingredients.
Make 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Check bottoms often.

title: hand-me-down chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat one minute at medium speed. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, and salt; add alternately with water to creamed mixture. Pour batter into two greased and floured eight-inch cake pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool; frost with chocolate frosting and decorate.

title: brie in pastry(appetizer)
directions: Mix in food processor or by hand into dough.
Wrap and refrigerate.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli in a greased baking dish.
Top with chicken. Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and soup.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Mix crumbs with butter and top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oreo cookie ice cream
directions: Whip the cream.
In large bowl beat egg yolks.
Stir in condensed milk, water and vanilla.
Fold in cookies and whipped cream.
Pour into 2-quart container. Freeze 6 hours, covered.

title: herbed pork chops
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Arrange pork chops on an 8-inch square dish.
Pour marinade over pork chops; cover and refrigerate 8 hours, turning meat occasionally.
Drain meat, discarding marinade.
Place chops on a lightly greased rack in broiler pan.
Broil 6 inches from heat with oven door partially open for 12 minutes.
Turn chops and broil 10 more minutes or until done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cool 'n easy watermelon pie
directions: Step 1:
Stir boiling water into gelatin in bowl 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Remove any remaining ice.

title: banana chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar in large bowl.
Add egg.
Beat in dry ingredients and mashed bananas.
Add chocolate chips and nuts. Mix well.
Drop rounded teaspoonful onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chess cake or chess squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter, 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 4 eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla and powdered sugar.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Allow to cool completely before serving.

title: melt-in-your-mouth biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients together until smooth and blended.
