Spoon dough into mini-muffin tins.
(Fill each hole about 3/4 full.)
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are nicely browned.
If using larger muffin tins, you may have to bake them about 15 minutes.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cook macaroni according to directions.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef over medium heat, approximately 25 minutes. Add other ingredients.
Lower heat and cook about 1 hour.
Freezes real well.

title: butter pecan brownies
directions: Mix cream cheese, melted butter, powdered sugar and 2 eggs and pour over first mixture.

title: jalapeno beef stew
directions: Brown stew beef; add onion and whatever you want to.
Cover with water.
Cook slow for approximately 1 hour or until meat is done and juice is thick.
Add jalapeno peppers and cook awhile. Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: german chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Use 8 x 14-inch pan that is greased and floured.
Spread coconut and pecans on bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Melt margarine, then add cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well. Spread over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: honey bee bars
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon; add honey, oil, egg and chopped nuts.
Mix with an electric beater only until ingredients are blended.
Press down in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 9 x 9-inch pan, depending on how thick you want your bars.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, no longer, they will be too hard.
While cake is still hot, mix glaze and spread on bars.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend the two mixes and beat well with electric mixer for 10 minutes.
Pour batter into 10-inch tube cake pan, greased with solid shortening and floured.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole. Layer with half of the sliced potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle with half the flour, salt, pepper and cheese.
Dot with half the butter.
Repeat layers.
Cover with milk.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until potatoes are tender and top is browned.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter; add sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and flour sifted with soda.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and with a wet fork flatten in a crisscross design. Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with remaining cheese and cornflakes and pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crisp little lemon cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Form into 1-inch balls, pressing firmly.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes, or until lightly golden brown around the edges.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: spinach and bacon salad
directions: Wash and drain spinach and lettuce.
Combine spinach, lettuce and bacon.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Heat Velveeta, chocolate and corn syrup in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture is melted. Gradually add sugar to chocolate mixture, beating with electric mixer on medium until smooth.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Smooth surface with spatula. Refrigerate several hours.
Cut into squares.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
In a small bowl, beat pumpkin, oil, juice, eggs and vanilla. Stir pumpkin mixture into flour mixture until well combined.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Turn into prepared pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Turn out of pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Use electric mixer or whisk.
Mix all ingredients well.
Must be well blended.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Crack eggs in a small bowl.
Mix with a fork.
Melt butter in a frying pan over low heat.
Pour in eggs.
Stir evenly until cooked.
Shake a little salt and pepper to taste.
Careful, not too much!

title: apple - onion yogurt dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand for 1 hour before serving.
Carrots may be reserved and sprinkled on top to decorate.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in sheet cake pan, 9 x 12-inch.
Add syrup and brown sugar.
Heat until it boils.
Then remove from heat. Arrange pineapple slices over syrup.
Then fill spaces with walnuts and cherries.
Mix cake as directed on box, using reserved juice as part of liquid.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: beef jerky
directions: Marinate for 1/2 hour.
Put on cookie sheet.
Place in oven for 4 to 6 hours at 140° to 150°.
Crack door slightly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together with zucchini being added last.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350° in greased loaf pans.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, butter and sugars; beat until creamy. Gradually beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over the top.
Put in oven for 3 minutes at 350°. Remove and run knife through to marbleize.
Return to oven and bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: northwest purple plum salad
directions: Wash plums, cut in half and remove seeds.
Using a cutting board and sharp knife, cut each half lengthwise and then 2 times crosswise.
(This keeps plums in firm even sized pieces, not possible with chopping.)
Bring sugar and water to boiling point. Then stir the gelatin into hot syrup.
Add orange juice and peel. Chill.
When it begins to thicken, stir in remaining ingredients. Pur into a 1 1/2-quart oiled mold or other dish.
Chill until firm. Turn out on a chilled plate and garnish with salad greens.
Serve with mayonnaise to which a little orange juice, peel and whipped cream have been added, if desired.

title: shrimp creole(makes 6 servings)
directions: Combine butter, onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in a 2- or 3-quart casserole.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 3 minutes. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt, sugar, chili powder and hot pepper sauce.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 7 minutes, stirring once.
Combine cornstarch with 2 teaspoons cold water.
Stir into casserole.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 3 minutes, stirring once.
Add shrimp.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 2 minutes or until shrimp is piping hot.
Serve with wild rice or plain boiled rice.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Melt oleo in boiling water. Add oats and beaten eggs. Mix flour and spices together. Blend with liquid mixture. Add sugar and mix with slotted spoon. Bake at 350°.

title: skillet barbecued burgers
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Form into six patties.
Press one onion slice in each. Heat Wesson oil in skillet and brown onion side of patties.
Pour off excess fat.
Turn patties and lemon slices, celery and remaining seasonings.
Pour on remaining 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes or until done.
Baste patties occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: soybean cheese salad
directions: Toss first three ingredients together.
Add enough yogurt to moisten.

title: orange-glazed pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops lightly with salt and pepper; dredge in flour.
Heat oil in a heavy skillet.
Brown pork chops on both sides.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix together and pour into greased muffin pans, filling only half full.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Makes about 12 muffins.
Baking time is 15 to 20 minutes.

title: skillet burgers
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and peppers; cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve on bun.

title: my favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend flour, peanut butter and salt. Add rest of ingredients and mix together. Drop a rounded teaspoonful of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet and press down with a fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese bits
directions: With mixer, blend cheese and butter until soft.
Sift flour and pepper; gradually work into cream mixture with spoon.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into 1 inch rounds.
Brush with egg whites.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in hot oven at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: nannie's crackers
directions: Mix together
all
ingredients, then pour over crackers in huge dish. Stir every 5 minutes for 1 hour. Store in Ziploc bag in refrigerator.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until soft (about 45 minutes at 425°).
Cut the top (lengthwise) off of each.
Scoop out potatoes and mash with sour cream, oleo, salt, pepper, onion, broccoli and 3/4 cup cheese.
Refill potato shells.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine. Add to spaghetti both soups and cheese cut into bite size pieces. Let cheese melt.
Put in a baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoon or roll into little balls on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 325°.

title: mexican casserole using chicken
directions: Layer tortillas and chicken alternately in greased casserole dish.
Combine 1 cup of cheese with all other ingredients.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: turnip greens
directions: Wash turnip greens several times, changing water each time. Put into a large pot; add about 1/2 pot of water and the salt. May add fatback, if you like.
Cook on medium heat until greens have cooked down and are tender.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except soda and water.
Soda and water mixture last.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: country captain from india
directions: Salt and flour chicken.
Fry in shortening until brown. Add all
others.
Bring to boiling, reduce to simmer and cook 30 minutes
or
until	chicken
is
tender.
Serve over rice. Sprinkle almonds on top.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar. Add remainder of ingredients in order given.
Beat well.
Place in well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake in cold oven at 325°.
Cook for 90 minutes and remove from pan when hot.

title: hearty bean soup
directions: Cook bacon in a large, heavy saucepan until crisp.
Drain and set aside.
Leave a small amount of drippings in pan (about 1 tablespoon).
Add green pepper, onion, carrot and garlic. Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes which have been mashed or cut into small pieces.
Stir in navy beans along with salt, pepper and sugar. Simmer 30 minutes to an hour.
Add crumbled bacon and parsley flakes.
Cook 5 minutes more.
This is delicious when made the day before and reheated slowly at serving time.

title: onion cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and milk, stirring constantly.
Add cheese.
Remove from heat and stir until cheese is melted.
Serve in bowls and add bread croutons.

title: wassail(hot christmas or holiday drink)
directions: Heat cider and cinnamon stick in a
large pan (a large double boiler works well). Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Keep hot over low heat or heat in small batches as guests arrive.
Makes 20 cups.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix
strawberry
soda pop with Eagle Brand milk.
Slice strawberries
into quarters and add to mixture.
Pour into a 1 gallon freezer and freeze according to freezer directions.

title: easy sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add green pepper, soup, 2 dashes of Worcestershire sauce and a squirt of mustard.
Add enough water to the consistency you like and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve on potato buns with green vegetable.

title: amber glow
directions: Press cream cheese into an 8 ounce plastic margarine tub or a small bowl.
Loosen edges with a spatula and invert onto the center of a shallow serving dish.
Smooth surface with a spatula. In a small bowl, mix preserves, mustard, horseradish and red pepper or hot pepper sauce until well blended.
Pour over cheese. Sprinkle with nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Tear chicken into bite size pieces and place on bottom of ungreased casserole dish.
Rinse and drain the frozen vegetables and pour over chicken.
Combine in small bowl 1 cup milk and cream of chicken soup.
Combine in small bowl, 1 cup of milk, Bisquick mix and melted margarine.
Pour slowly over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate peanut butter pizza
directions: Combine in a large bowl and blend well all the ingredients. After combined, press into a pizza pan, forming a rim along edge. Bake crust 10 minutes in a 350° oven, then sprinkle with 2 cups miniature marshmallows and 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes until marshmallows are puffy and lightly brown.
Cool and cut.
Store in tightly covered container.
(A 15 x 9 pan will also work.)

title: russian tea
directions: Boil the water and sugar 5 minutes. Add cloves and tea (tie in bag).
Boil 5 minutes more. Simmer 10 minutes. Add orange and lemon juices. Serve hot or cold.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in a nonstick skillet, no need to add any oil.
After chops are brown, baste both sides with prepared mustard.
Pour a can of chicken with rice soup, plus 1 soup can of water over the chops.
Pour in 3/4 to 1 cup of uncooked rice. Bring to a boil; cover and turn to low.
Cook until liquid is absorbed, approximately 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Mix all together.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry-pretzel dessert
directions: Combine butter with 3 tablespoons sugar and pretzels.
Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; let cool.
Cream 1 cup sugar with cream cheese; add 1 small container Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel mixture.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add frozen strawberries.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill.
Top with dollops of Cool Whip, if desired.

title: "gone too soon" cookies
directions: Cream the oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and finally chocolate chips. Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.
Nut kernels may be placed on top before baking.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Cook sausage in a skillet until browned; drain and set aside. Combine next 5 ingredients, mixing well. Cut in shortening until it resembles coarse meal. Dissolve yeast in warm water (105° to 115°).
Let stand 5 minutes. Add yeast to buttermilk, stirring. Add to dry ingredients, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Knead in sausage. Turn dough out onto a floured surface.
Knead lightly. Roll out dough and cut into rounds.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: the children's favorite skillet supper
directions: Cut steaks into 1 1/2-inch wide strips and dredge in flour. Brown in oil in a large (at last 10-inch) skillet.
Lay aside on a plate.
Cook and stir onion in oil until tender.
Drain.

title: dijon vinaigrette
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar in blender.
Add salt, garlic, basil, black pepper, hot sauce and onion; whirl.
With machine running, add oil, one tablespoon at a time.
Chill.
Keeps several weeks.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: spinach braid
directions: Mix spinach, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and garlic. Spray cookie sheet and place crescent rolls on cookie sheet. Pinch edges together.
Lay filling down in the middle of the dough and put the Provolone cheese over the filling.
Fold over the edges of the crescent rolls to cover the filling.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.
Slice to serve.

title: orange balls
directions: Reserve 1/2 c. wafers.

title: strawberry butter
directions: The fruit and butter should be at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add berries and refrigerate.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Heat salted water to a boil.
Add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes until stems are almost tender. Drain.
Place broccoli in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat oven to 400°.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon until evenly brown. Crumble and set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Arrange in a dish.
Combine cheese, eggs, mayonnaise, soup and onion.
Spread over broccoli and cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
One-half cup sour cream may be substituted for mayonnaise, if desired.

title: candy legs
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in a double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Stir until well coated.
Drop onto wax paper to harden.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: *Would recommend from nil to 1/2 cup sugar.
Dates, coconut and Rice Krispies supply sufficient sweetener in my opinion.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Pour dressing over bean mixture and chill for a few hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Add sugar and cream until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, while mixing.
Sift baking powder with flour, then add to mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavorings and mix.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mexican layered dip or salad
directions: Open beans and season to taste with garlic powder and chili powder or salsa or seasoning.
I usually fix this in "X" baking dish.
Cover layer of beans with layer of chopped onion.
Cover with sour cream dip.
Sprinkle cheese, lettuce and fresh tomatoes on top.
Serve with corn chips.

title: hallie's pineapple - coconut pie
directions: Mix
all together and pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add chopped celery and pepper slices. Fry all until lightly browned.
Add onion and water in pan to cover ingredients.
Simmer with lid until meat is tender (1/2 hour).
Add soy sauce, mushrooms and chopped tomato.
Thicken with cornstarch. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add flour, soda, salt, eggs, cinnamon and buttermilk.
Bake at 350° until done.
Can refrigerate dough up to 3 weeks and make them fresh occasionally.

title: zesty chicken 'n rice
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken.
Place flour, mix and chili powder in paper or plastic bag.
Add chicken and shake until coated with flour mixture.
Heat oil; brown chicken.
Drain tomatoes, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 1/2 cups of liquid. Add tomatoes, liquid, onion, green pepper, rice, salt and pepper to chicken.
Stir, making certain rice is covered with liquid. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Cook over low heat until chicken is tender, about 40 minutes.

title: chili with beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer.

title: lithuanian mushroom bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Simmer the mushrooms and onion in the margarine over low heat, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Place in shallow pan.
Mix together the sour cream, yogurt, flour, salt and pepper.
Pour over mushrooms.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package instructions.
Microwave rice works great.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add celery and onion.
Saute lightly, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cooked rice and Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Add undiluted celery soup, broccoli, salt and pepper.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eclair torte
directions: Mix pudding with milk; let it set up slightly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place a layer of whole graham crackers.
Put a layer of pudding mix over it, then another layer of graham crackers, then the rest of the pudding and, finally, another layer of graham crackers.
Melt the jar of hot fudge topping a little; put on top of the graham crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 325° until done.

title: quail in cream sauce
directions: Put birds in Dutch oven or pressure cooker.
Add salt, pepper, onion, celery and water.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender or pressure cook 20 minutes at 15 pounds.
Remove birds from liquid and cool.
Break meat into small pieces.
Stir into Cream Sauce (following) and heat.
Serve at once over toast.

title: chinese chicken
directions: You will need 16 skewers about 6-inches long.

title: creamy cheese and bacon spread
directions: Combine bacon, cream cheese and marmalade.
Refrigerate mixture.
Allow spread to reach room temperature at serving time. Serve with celery sticks, apple slices (Cortlands keep their color) and crackers.
Dress tray with red and green grapes and parsley.

title: grandma charrons hot apricots
directions: Drain apricots.
Place in a large 2-quart casserole, round side up.
Cover with brown sugar (6 to 8 tablespoons) and with dots of butter.
Add on top crumbled Ritz crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend together Crisco, sugars, salt and eggs.
Add peanut butter.
Stir in flour.
Form the dough in small balls and place on greased sheet.
Flatten with fork, crisscross.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: chicken and vegetable bake
directions: *May use broccoli, cauliflower, carrots and cut green beans.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Combine in bowl and microwave on low for 1 hour.

title: johnny cake
directions: Cream the sugar, oleo and eggs.
Add the soda to the sour milk and then add to the first mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° until brown and the edges are pulled away from the pan (about 30 to 40 minutes).

title: orange bowknots
directions: Combine scalded milk, shortening and sugar; cool to lukewarm. Add yeast, orange juice and peel.
Add flour and mix to soft dough. Cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: baked rockwell beans
directions: After sorting and washing beans, put them on in cold water and cook for a long period of time until beans are tender (possible 3 to 4 hours).
After beans are tender, add remaining ingredients.

title: weenie gravy
directions: Cook onion in oil until clear and soft; add flour.
Mix well. Add tomato sauce, barbecue sauce and water.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Chop hot dogs up 1/4 to 1/8-inch.
Add to mixture and cook another 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: toasted toffee pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs and almond paste in a large bowl.
Beat until blended.
Add brown sugar, 3/4 c. corn syrup, and melted butter, whisking until blended.
Stir in 1-1/2 c. chopped pecans.
Pour into pie crust and place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put cream cheese in a bowl.
Cut chipped beef in small pieces. Add to cream cheese.
Add chopped green onion, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Mix all together very well.
Shape into a ball.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and arrange 4 to 5 on bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed; drain and squeeze excess water out. Squeeze water out of artichokes.
Saute onion in butter until onion is clear.
Add sour cream.
Spread bottom of casserole with half of spinach-artichoke mixture.
Spread half of sour cream and onion mixture on top, then spread 1/2 cup of cheese.
Repeat same for second layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dressing for smoke-barbecued turkey
directions: Simmer giblets, neck,
1 medium onion, celery, salt and pepper in 1
quart water until tender.
Saute celery, 1 onion, mushrooms and
parsley
in
butter.	Combine
bread	crumbs, cornbread, chopped
giblets,
sauteed	vegetables, sage, salt, pepper and broth
from
giblets
in
a
large	bowl.
Place in casserole; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
May use rest of broth for gravy.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place chicken breasts into baking dish. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
In a saucepan, combine the tomatoes, cornstarch and oregano; cook on a medium heat, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Pour heated sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes more.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: tex mex enchiladas
directions: Chop onions and chilies, mince garlic.
Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat, add onions and saute until soft.
Stir in flour, chicken broth, chilies, garlic and salt to taste and cumin and simmer 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a rectangular baking dish.
Grate cheese, slice green onions.
Put some chicken in each tortilla along with some onion mixture and 3 tablespoons of grated cheese.
Roll up tortillas and put in baking dish seam side down.
Pour the remaining sauce over them and then the cream.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and green onions.
Bake 20 minutes and garnish with tomatoes.

title: banana slush
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar and water.
Bring to a boil; boil 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal and cheese in medium bowl, then stir in oil until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in water until well mixed. On floured surface use your hands, form with your hands and then use cookie cutter, transfer to ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken chile casserole
directions: Combine soup, onion, chilies and sour cream.
Spread some in casserole pan.
Layer tortilla strips, soup mixture, cheese and chicken.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
If you prefer it even spicier, you can add picante sauce when serving.

title: peek-a-boo squares
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add extracts, then add flour and mix well.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Beat egg; stir in remaining ingredients, mixing just to moisten.
Pour into 12 greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cream cheese must be very soft.
Drain water from can of artichoke hearts.
Cut up hearts and add cream cheese.
Mix well. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 9 or 10-inch glass pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve while warm with celery, carrots or crackers.

title: pork chops and peas
directions: Brown pork chops.
Add peas, saving liquid and adding also, to tomato soup in separate bowl.
Add to this mixture the chopped onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Add to pork chops.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine milk, water and pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of the wafers, bananas and pudding.
Let chill.

title: merry mincemeaters
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon and salt together. Cream the butter and sugar together well. Blend in the unbeaten egg and almond extract. Beat well. Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Roll out half of the dough on greased 10 x 8-inch baking sheet. Spread with 1 1/2 cups prepared mincemeat.
Roll out remaining dough to 10 x 8-inches.
Invert dough over mincemeat.
Brush with reserved egg white, slightly beaten. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour and seasoned salt.
Cook in small amount of oil.
Steam broccoli.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Toss with 1/4 cup of Butter Buds and juice of 1 lemon.
Put on platter. Add broccoli.
Lay chicken on top and arrange lemon slices around chicken.
Sprinkle it all with lemon pepper and parsley.

title: my favorite sweet potato recipe
directions: Cook potatoes in a large saucepan in
enough salt water to cover.
Cook about 15 minutes or until
tender.
Drain
and set aside.
Spread pie filling in an 8	x
x
2-inch baking dish. Arrange cooked potatoes on top.
In a small mixing bowl stir together cranberry sauce, apricot
preserves
and
orange marmalade.	Spoon over sweet potatoes.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers or rye crisps.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well until sugar is mixed well. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until thick.
Cook in open pot. Put in jars and seal.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: baked chunky vegetables
directions: Cut vegetables into large, chunky pieces (more than a bite) and place in baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over vegetables and mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 20 minutes or until desired texture.
Stir occasionally while cooking.

title: guacamole
directions: Chop tomato and slice onions.
Mince garlic and pepper.
Halve and peel avocados and cut into cubes.
Squeeze 1 teaspoon lime juice over avocados and toss.
Add other ingredients, serve chilled.

title: chick and chips
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Empty soup into a 1-quart casserole dish and add milk; mix thoroughly.
Stir in chicken (or tuna) and 1 cup of potato chips and peas.
Sprinkle top with the remaining 1/4 cup of chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Very good served over rice.

title: chicken breasts with asparagus
directions: Brown the chicken breasts in 2 tablespoons oil in heavy skillet.
Partially cook asparagus.
Layer in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put chicken breasts on top of asparagus.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, onions, lemon juice and curry powder.
Spread on top of chicken pieces.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand for 5 minutes, until cheese melts, before serving.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix ingredients and fill peppers.
Stand in baking dish in which a small amount of water has been added.
Cover dish and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: lemon dessert
directions: To prepare crust, mix flour, chopped nuts and butter.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water until dissolved. Add juice and stir. Put in the refrigerator until set. Mix with spoon until in small chunks and add softened Cool Whip.

title: spinach soup
directions: Puree spinach in blender.
Put bouillon cubes and cream in saucepan and scald, stirring until cubes are dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
May be served topped with chopped hard-cooked eggs.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, vanilla and sugars until fluffy.
Add spices. Add flour a little at a time; add nuts and zucchini.
Bake in 2 loaf pans 1 hour at 350°.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter at medium speed of mixer until light and fluffy. Add 1 cup powdered sugar and salt. Mix well. Stir in flour. Add water, vanilla and nuts, stirring well.

title: cherry topped cheese pie
directions: Beat together softened cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Top with canned cherry pie filling.
Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: suffsoof (tabouleh)
directions: Soak the bulgur in hot water for at least 30 minutes.
(Bulk will more than double.)

While this is soaking, chop the parsley, scallions, tomatoes and mint and place together in a large bowl. Squeeze as much water as possible from the bulgur between your two hands and toss in the bowl with the vegetables.
Mix well to combine all ingredients.
At the last minute, add the pulped cucumber, the lemon juice, oil and seasonings.
Mix well and taste.
More lemon may be needed as the salad should have a distinctly lemony taste.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook together sugar, cornstarch and water in double boiler until thickened. Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O.
Cool. Fill baked pie crust with raw strawberries.
Pour the sauce over the berries and place in refrigerator until set.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in unsalted water until tender.
Drain and place in a bowl with pepper and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring mixture to a boil.
Pour over carrots.
May be served warm or cold.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine crabmeat with all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well. Spoon into small baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Scoop with crackers or chips.

title: roasted peanuts
directions: Combine ingredients and boil until all the water is absorbed. Stir frequently, if not constantly.
Spread on greased cookie sheet (preferably one with low sides).
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Stir and salt 2 times during baking.

title: southwest white chili
directions: Heat oil in a 2 to 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove chicken, cover and keep warm.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Scald milk, stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Put warm water in large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add milk mixture, starter and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Turn onto floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until double in size (about 1 hour).
Punch dough down, divide into 3 equal parts.
Form each piece into a roll.
Place in loaf pans with sharp knife.
Cut dough in a crisscross fashion on top.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplants, cube and boil until tender.
Drain and mash. Saute ground meat with onion until no longer pink.
In large bowl, mix all of the ingredients, except 1/2 c. cheese for topping. Pour mixture in 9-inch x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes until set.

title: corn pudding
directions: Whisk together flour, milk, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Add corn and stir.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that has been buttered and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Spread thinly on cookie sheet.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine egg, 1/4 cup of the soup, uncooked rice, onion powder and pepper. Add beef; mix well. Shape into 20 meatballs. Place in a large skillet.

title: guacamole
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth.
Chill.
Serve with chips.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast
in
1/4 cup warm water.
Combine sugar, oil and buttermilk;
stir
in yeast.
Stir in flour.
Knead as if making
biscuits.
Roll
to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place 1 patty of butter on each roll and fold over.
Place
rolls
on
heavily
greased cookie sheet and let stand, covered, in
a
warm
place
until
ready
to serve (30 minutes to 3 hours).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Microwave the first 3 ingredients on High for 3 minutes. Stir. Add the nuts and marshmallows. Stir.
Put in wax paper lined 13 x 2 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into small pieces.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add dash of salt.
Add half and half and cook in double boiler until mixture thickens.
Strain through sieve.
Let cool.
Add whipping cream, vanilla extract and enough milk to fill to line
of 1 gallon freezer.

title: george washington pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add lemon and vanilla flavoring.

title: "ghivetch"" vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 3-quart casserole, combine cauliflower, squash, carrots, celery, onions, bell pepper, beans, potato and peas; set aside.
In small saucepan, over medium-high heat, bring broth, oil, garlic and bay leaf to a boil.
Remove from heat; pour over vegetables.
Cover tightly.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, until potatoes are almost tender, stirring once or twice.
Add tomatoes, parsley and dill.
Cook, covered, 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple stack cake
directions: Divide cake mix batter into 5 equal parts.
Pour the equal parts into greased cake pans (round).
Bake at 350° or until brown. Cool each layer, then between each layer, add apple butter or applesauce.
Continue until you use all layers.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples in thin slices and cover the bottom of a buttered pan with them.
Combine flour, sugar and butter and beat well. Spread mixture over apples and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: southern style spareribs
directions: Combine water, mustard and pepper sauce; brush on ribs. Empty seasonings and coating mixture into shaker bag.
Shake 1 or 2 ribs
at
a
time.	Arrange
ribs
close together, sides touching in 13
x
9-inch pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes for one hour at 350° or until tender in center. Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out potato carefully as to not tear skins.
Mash potatoes with mixer; add half and half and continue to beat until smooth.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Mixture should be somewhat softer than regular mashed potatoes to prevent drying out when baking again.
Fill skin shells with mashed potato mixture and arrange on cookie sheet.
Top each with extra grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Great with steaks.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini (steam or boil).
Cook carrots and onion in 4 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Place vegetables in 1 1/2-quart casserole with soup, sour cream and 1 1/2 cups of the stuffing.
Mix well.
Then melt the remaining butter and toss with the remaining stuffing.
Sprinkle that mixture on top of the prepared vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. In large bowl, combine cake mix and butter at low speed until crumbly. Reserve 1 1/4 cups crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add milk and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Arrange blueberries evenly over batter.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Crush cornflakes to 3/4 cup.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Add egg and 1/4 cup barbecue sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly. Add ground beef.
Mix only until combined.
Shape into 6 oval patties, 3/4 inch thick.
Place on lightly greased or foil-lined pan.
Brush with remaining barbecue sauce.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes for medium done, shorter or longer baking time to preference.
Do not turn while baking.

title: apricot-sauced ribs
directions: Ribs can be cooked on grill or in oven 1 1/2 hours, turning occasionally.
Mix remaining ingredients together in blender. Brush ribs generously with sauce and continue to cook for 30 minutes, basting and turning often.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Prepare
rice
according
to package directions.
Slice sausage and brown in skillet.
Add the kidney beans and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: yams hawaiian style(microwave recipe)
directions: Slice yams into 1/2-inch thick pieces. Combine with pineapple, butter, sugar and cinnamon in a 2-quart casserole. Microwave on High 4 minutes; stir. Sprinkle top with nuts and brown sugar. Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes. If dish is not hot and topping not melted after 2 minutes, rotate dish 1/4 turn. Continue to microwave. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: homemade ravioli
directions: Brown meat, remove from heat, drain, add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and cool.
Whip together cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla. Pour milk into bowl and cool in freezer until crystals form around edges. Then whip milk until peaks form.
Add jello and cheese mixture into whipped milk.
Roll graham crackers into fine crumbs. Add 3 tablespoons of sugar and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Put 1/2 of crumbs on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread cheese mixture over top of crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Store in refrigerator several hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender and lightly brown.
Cool completely.
Beat eggs well.
Add milk, cans of corn, cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add onions and cheese (reserve some cheese to sprinkle over the top of the casserole).
Pour mixture into 3-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store tightly covered.
Use 2 teaspoons mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: turkey in the bundt(light and souffle-like; an excellent way to use leftover turkey!)
directions: Place 3 cups bread cubes in bottom of greased 12-cup Bundt pan.
Place turkey evenly over bread, then spread Swiss cheese over turkey.
Sprinkle with dry onions.
Top with remaining 3 cups bread cubes.
Combine beaten eggs with milk and seasonings.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Place Bundt pan in pan of water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan of water and bake an additional 10 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes. With plastic spatula, lift turkey mixture away from edges of pan and remove.
Serve with buttered peas in center of ring, if desired.
Garnish tray with apple rings.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions. Add cream cheese and beat well until smooth.
Place in pie crust on sides and bottom leaving center hollow. Put pie filling in center of pie and chill.

title: grilled carrots
directions: Place carrots on a large double layer of aluminum foil; fold up sides to form a container.
Sprinkle carrots with onion flakes, garlic salt and pepper.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a small jar or measuring cup; pour over carrots.
Wrap foil tightly around carrots to make a packet.
Marinate 2 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove carrots from foil; place on hinged grill or on a rack 4 inches from source of heat.
Grill 45 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Doesn't seem like a lot, but remember, all the ingredients were fresh.
The ketchup was homemade, and so was the tomato sauce.

title: taco sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients, except onions, together for 45 minutes. Add onions and heat for an additional 5 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal in a hot water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes 9 pints.

title: italian biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Frost.
Makes approximately 150 to 160 biscuits.

title: curry chicken delight(makes 8 servings)
directions: Rinse chicken.
Coat chicken pieces with flour.
In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon on paper toweling; crumble and set aside.
Reserve drippings.
Add chicken to skillet; slowly brown chicken on all sides in hot drippings about 10 minutes. Transfer chicken to an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake chicken, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Combine honey, mustard, salt and curry powder.
Drizzle over chicken in baking dish. Bake, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes more.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: pork cutlets italiano
directions: Mix together seasonings.
Pat
half
of
mixture on one side of cutlets.
Press remaining mixture on other side.
Heat approximately 3 tablespoons oil in pan.
Brown cutlets on both sides.
Bake in same pan in oven for 10 to 15 minutes at 325°. Serve with spaghetti.
Serves 4.

title: christmas grab bag bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together margarine, cake mix and 1 egg.
Press into bottom of a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat together 2 eggs, cream cheese and sugar.
Add coconut and nuts. Pour over cake mixture.
Bake 45 minutes until golden brown.
Cool in pan on rack.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Place in 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.
Good with ham dishes.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and whipped topping. Add other ingredients and mix all together.
Chill.

title: regal chocolate sauce
directions: Microwave chocolate and water in microwavable bowl on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in sugar.
Microwave 1 minute.
Stir.
Cook 2 minutes longer; stir in margarine and vanilla.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: k. c. baked casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions to taste.
In casserole, add green beans, kidney beans, pork and beans and lima beans with browned ground beef.
Mix with barbecue sauce and cheese.
Do not add any seasonings or spices.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage; drain grease.
Put green pepper and onion (chopped up) in dish.
Mix together beaten eggs with a little canned milk.
Put into other ingredients.
Put in oven and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, except sugar.
Mix together pumpkin, sugar, eggs, oil and nuts.
Add a small box of instant coconut pudding and mix in dry ingredients.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters; set aside.
Melt butter in microwave (covered).
Pour butter over biscuits.
Add other ingredients. Mix until biscuits are well coated.
In a well-greased Bundt pan, pour mixture evenly.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together (use blender or mixer).
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Advance preparation:
Combine all ingredients except chicken pieces.
Turn into 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish that had been sprayed with pam.
Place chicken on top.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover, chill.
(May be done a day ahead.)
Before serving, bake, covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir rice, sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes to 1 hour more until liquid has been absorbed and chicken is tender.
Stir rice again before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix meat, egg, onion, salt, ketchup and sauce.
Mix well and shape into 6 patties.
Dip in flour and brown in skillet.
Add oil or it will stick.
Put into baking dish and add soup and water. Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.
Easy and good.

title: holiday pie
directions: Heat cranberry cocktail to boiling.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce and mix thoroughly.
Cool in refrigerator for 2 hours, then pour into shell and let set overnight.
Top the servings with Cool Whip.
(Since the filling is cooled thoroughly, it doesn't soak in the crust.)

title: peanut butter buddy bars
directions: Mix peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Blend in flour.
Stir in 1 cup milk chocolate morsels.
Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven, or until edges begin to brown.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In bowl, combine spinach, artichokes, cream, salt, pepper and 1/3 cup Parmesan.

title: mousse in a minute
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on package using cold milk. Fold in whipped topping and spoon into dessert dishes.
Garnish with additional whipped topping if desired.
Makes 2 2/3 cups or 5 servings.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Place rack in lowest position.
Place pie in preheated 425° oven.
Spoon apple filling into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Toss hot spaghetti with oil.
Combine eggs and Parmesan cheese. Stir into spaghetti.
Pour into pie plate.
Press to form a crust. Spread Ricotta cheese over crust.
Top with sauce.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into wedges.

title: banana bread
directions: Put all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, yogurt, bananas and milk.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients and add liquids.
Stir until mixed well with a wooden spoon.
Pour into a greased bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue cod
directions: Spray glass baking dish with Pam.
Place cod in dish and cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes, turning once. Remove and pour off any liquid.
Pour barbecue sauce over fish; cover again with plastic wrap and microwave for 2 minutes more on High.
Check fish for doneness.
Return fish to microwave for 1 more minute at a time until fish flakes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, combine soups, rice, water and butter.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice mixture and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until tender.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage; drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard. Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with bread cubes, then sausage and then cheese.
Dot with butter.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: wonderful creamy broccoli soup
directions: Cook noodles for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not salt water.
Drain. Saute onions, celery and carrots in butter until soft.
In large kettle, bring chicken broth to boil.
Add frozen broccoli, ham, parsley, garlic and veggies.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Add cooked noodles and cheese.
Reduce heat to low.
When cheese is melted, add milk.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Cook sauce ingredients in saucepan until bubbly.
Add 3 tablespoons lemon juice.

title: hidden valley ranch pasta primavera
directions: Steam vegetables until crisp-tender.
Cook fettucine in chicken broth until tender; drain.
Combine fettucine with vegetables; add basil and salad dressing and toss gently. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
May add zucchini, mushrooms or other vegetables.
Also good made ahead and reheated.

title: corn relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions.
Mix all together.
Put in large kettle.
Cook about 25 minutes.
Fill pint jars to one-inch of top seal.
Put in water bath.
When this boils, process 5 minutes. Makes 8 pints.

title: hot pepper mustard
directions: First mix up 1 cup of flour and 3 cups of water, cook making a thick mixture.
Set aside until later.

title: orange tailgate salad
directions: Arrange lettuce leaves on flat platter.
Arrange fruit over lettuce.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine cranberries, oranges, rind and water.
Cook until soft.
Run through sieve.
Add sugar and pineapple.
Bring to a boil.
Cook a bit and add gelatin.
Stir.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Melt margarine in a large long Pyrex dish. Place chicken in bottom of dish and add salt and pepper. Pour in soup and chicken broth. Set aside. Mix self-rising flour and buttermilk. Drop by spoonfuls on top of chicken mixture. Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: 5 salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: cucumber and tomato salad
directions: Peel and cube cucumbers, tomatoes and onion (onion, smaller). Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix with mixer until smooth. Great with raw veggies.

title: frog legs in mushroom sauce
directions: Cut several frog legs into pieces; place in saucepan.
Cover with boiling water or light stock.
Add the lemon slices, white pepper, celery, onion and parsley.
Simmer, covered, until tender. Drain.
Melt the butter or margarine in saucepan.
Add the sliced mushrooms.
Stir in the flour.
Stir in slowly the chicken stock or stock from cooking the frog legs.
Correct the seasonings.

title: oven baked pasta casserole
directions: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
In a large frying pan, saute the beef, garlic and oil until beef is tender; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients except pasta.
Simmer the mixture while pasta is cooking.
Drain pasta and pour all into 3-quart baking dish.
Mix carefully.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with your favorite shredded cheese.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Cream butter and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in separate bowl the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Stir in oats.
Drop by spoonful on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice.
Cook broccoli.
Mix all ingredients; pour into greased casserole dish.
Heat in oven until bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour.
Stir into sliced apples.

Pour into prepared pie crust that has been sprinkled with about 2 tablespoons of bread crumbs on the bottom. Dot with butter and cover with top crust, that has been perforated to allow steam to escape.
Top crust may be brushed with milk and sprinkled with sugar, if desired.
Place pie on lowest shelf in the oven for a crisp crust.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in a 425° oven. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: garlicky potatoes
directions: Stir salad dressing mix into potatoes. Serve immediately. Top with pat of butter, if desired. Serve with grilled or broiled steaks, chops, chicken or fish.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Bring to a boil the first 5 ingredients.
Pour boiled mixture over cabbage, peppers and onions.
Let cool overnight.
Will keep 10 days.

title: molded tuna salad
directions: Add water to gelatin.
Place over boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add other ingredients.
Mold.

title: cabbage ramen salad
directions: Toast, in a 325° oven for 10 minutes, the sesame seed and almonds.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Add dressing just before serving:

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon, draining off all fat except enough to saute onion.
In large Dutch oven, combine meat and all other ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: pulled mints
directions: Mix all in pan.
Cook until it cracks in cold water.
Pour on cold buttered marble.
Add oil of peppermint.
Pull.
Cut with scissors.
Store in tin overnight.
Makes 1 pound.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla. Then add dry ingredients.
Add sour cream and nuts.
Pour into greased floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil vegetables, margarine and water for 5 minutes.
Combine in a casserole with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, adding water, if needed.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Half zucchini lengthwise.
Scoop out zucchini, leaving a 3/4-inch shell.
Saute beef and onion.
Add scooped out zucchini. Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add rice.
Pack into shells.
Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice. Pour over stuffed zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry ice cream pie
directions: Combine gingersnap crumbs, sugar and melted butter in bowl. Mix until thoroughly blended.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in butter, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes or until toasted.
Set aside to cool.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 1 1/2 to 2 gallon hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze about 10 minutes or until ice cream is thick.
Remove dasher and add pecans to ice cream mixture.
Return dasher.
Freeze until firm according to freezer instructions.
Let ripen at least 1 hour.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons.

title: lo-cal vegie dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise in medium size mixing bowl with sour cream or plain yogurt.
Blend well.
Add dill, paprika and finely chopped green onions to taste.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours. Wash and chop vegies (dipper size) and arrange on plate for serving.
This dip is also excellent with potato chips or crackers.

title: spicy beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, combine the beef broth, soy sauce, cornstarch and mustard and stir until the cornstarch is dissolved.
Set aside.
Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
In a nonstick wok or large nonstick skillet, warm the oil over medium-high heat until hot, but not smoking.
Add the broccoli, cauliflower, onion and garlic and stir until the vegetables are crisp-tender and onion begins to brown, 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir the cornstarch mixture again and pour into wok.
Stir in beef, red pepper flakes and black pepper and stir-fry until the sauce thickens and the beef is heated through, 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and baking soda.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes in 375° oven.

title: macaroni baked with spaghetti sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni.
Drain well.
Layer macaroni, sauce and cheese alternately in a 1 1/2-quart casserole, ending with layer of cheese.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and surface is lightly browned.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat again.
Beat in margarine and vanilla.
Add flour and beat well.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into two greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown. Serve warm or cold.
Add a bit of whipped topping to each serving if desired.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into the creamed mixture.
Form dough into tiny balls.
Press out each ball with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen cookies.

title: seven layer yummy bars
directions: Melt butter. Stir in graham crackers.
Pat crumb mixture evenly in bottom of an ungreased 9 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Layer, in order, chocolate pieces, butterscotch pieces, coconut and walnuts. Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze.
Remove 30 minutes before serving.

title: layered tortilla casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic; drain. Add taco seasoning and mix according to directions on package. Add chili powder.

title: french onion soup(microwave)
directions: In 3 quart casserole, place onions and butter; cover. Microwave on High 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Add broth, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes.
Spoon soup into 6 individual bowls and top each serving with 1 slice toasted bread.
Divide cheese evenly among servings (1/4 cup per serving).
Microwave up to 3 bowls at a time, allowing 3/4 to 1 minute per serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Mix with Cool Whip and pour in pie crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix everything together but Doritos.
Layer it, ending with the Doritos on top.
Cover it with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Kids love this dish, especially with tacos.
Enjoy!

title: hot wassail
directions: Mix and simmer covered 20 minutes stirring occasionally. Yields:
15-18 servings.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Bring sugar, salt, vinegar and 1 cup water to a boil.
Add softened gelatin.
Cool.
Add lemon juice and onion.
Next add asparagus, celery, pimento and nuts.
Place in individual molds or a 9 x 9-inch dish to congeal.
Serves 9.

title: fudge turtles
directions: Place the pecans, caramels and milk in a double boiler and melt.
Drop on buttered paper and cool until hard.
Melt the chocolate chips and paraffin.
When caramel is hard, dip in the chocolate and set back on waxed paper.

title: macho choco cookies
directions: Combine the flour, cocoa and salt and set aside.
Line cookie sheets with foil.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and chocolate syrup; mix well.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and oats; mix.
Drop by heaping tablespoonful onto pans.
Bake for 10 minutes; rotate trays and switch shelves.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from trays.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients, then add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Fold in oatmeal and then raisins.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet with tablespoon amount.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: pears au chocolate
directions: Place 2 pear halves in each of 4 serving dishes.
Stir mint extract into pudding.
Spoon pudding over pears.
If desired, top each serving with frozen whipped topping.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Layer Tater Tots in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch brownie pan.
Top with ground meat.
Add a layer of cheese. Do another layer of Tater Tots, meat and cheese.
Empty can of soup into bowl; add 1 can of water.
Mix well and pour over casserole.
Cook according to directions on Tater Tot bag.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and vegetables until soft.
Smash with fork and let cool.
Then add milk and margarine.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir graham cracker crumbs into butter and pat over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle coconut on top; then drizzle condensed milk over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300° for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pink salmon
directions: Drain salmon; reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
In a bowl, combine salmon, egg and onion.
Add flour.
Mix baking powder liquid; stir into salmon mixture.
Make into patties.
Fry in hot Crisco. Serve hot.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Fold Cool Whip into milk and lemon juice mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into crust and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans until done, reducing time slightly; drain well, reserving 2 cups water.
Set green beans aside.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add creamer; gradually add reserved hot water and stir to blend.
Cook over medium heat (stir so as not to stick), until mixture bubbles and thickens.
Stir in seasonings and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Add cooked beans and water chestnuts, mixing well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly and golden.
Garnish with onion rings or chow mein noodles.

title: ruby red frost(serves 13 cups)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a punch bowl, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Stir in ice.
Add ginger ale, stirring gently. Scoop sherbet into punch bowl.
Garnish, if desired.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters, reserving liquid.
Mix crumbs and butter. Grease casserole and line bottom with 1/2 of the crumbs.
Add half of the oysters; sprinkle lightly with nutmeg, pepper and parsley. Repeat crumbs, oysters layer and season.
Combine Worcestershire sauce, salt and liquid.
Pour over casserole.
Top with crumb mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat on high speed the cream cheese, milk and pudding mix until smooth and creamy.
Fold in pineapple (drained) and spread on cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: can't fail fudge
directions: Combine marshmallows, milk, butter, sugar and salt in a large saucepan.
Stir until mixture comes to a full boil.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add chocolate, beating until melted.
Fold in vanilla.
Add nuts. Pour into greased 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Chill until firm.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll rolls and lay out flat on large cookie sheet.
Bake as directed.
Cool.
Mix together the cream cheese, dressing mix and Miracle whip and spread on cooled crust.
Shred 1 cup each carrots, broccoli, radishes, mushrooms, red and green pepper and black and/or green olives.
Sprinkle on top of cream cheese mixture in layers.
Refrigerate for a few hours.

title: world famous meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put in loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips of bacon if you like that flavor.
Pour over all an 8 ounce can of tomato sauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: deluxe cream cheese pound cake
directions: Allow butter, margarine, and cream cheese to soften and then cream together.
Slowly add the sugar until well creamed and fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time, mixing well until light and fluffy. Add 3 cups sifted flour, mixing well.
Finally, add vanilla and stir in well.
Pour into a well-greased bundt pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325 degrees.
Cool 10 minutes before flipping out of pan. Refrigerate cake to make it yummy.

title: apple pudding
directions: Pare, core and slice apples into deep casserole.
Mix together lemon juice, water, cinnamon and 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Add to apples.
Combine remaining sugar with flour and salt; work in the butter with a pastry blender or finger tips until the mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Sprinkle this over apples and pat smooth.

title: peanut butter jems
directions: Combine margarine and peanut butter in saucepan until melted. Add graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan lightly buttered.
Melt the 1/2 stick of margarine with the chocolate morsels.
Pour over the peanut butter mixture.
Put in the refrigerator until set.
Cut into fudge size pieces.
Cut the squares before chocolate gets too hard to slice.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: Preheat grill to medium.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray (need a small hole rack so vegetables won't fall through).
Cut onion in 8 wedges, leaving a portion of the root end attached. Place vegetables on rack.
Grill approximately 6 - 12 minutes or until desired doneness.
Remove to serving platter.
Serve with ranch or honey mustard dressing as a dip. Serves 4.

title: blueberry supreme
directions: In a buttered baking dish, layer ingredients in this order: pineapple (do not drain), blueberries, cake mix, margarine and pecans.
Bake according to cake mix directions.
Serve warm or cool with Cool Whip.

title: mexican dip
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish. Spread refried beans over bottom of dish. Mix taco seasoning and sour cream in a separate bowl and blend entirely. Spoon sour cream mixture over refried beans. Pour jar of salsa over mixture and top with Mexican shredded cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips. This is a great appetizer!

title: squash relish
directions: Soak squash, onions and peppers in salt and ice water for 1 hour.
Drain and rinse; rinse second time and drain.
Boil sugar, vinegar, turmeric and celery seed for 3 minutes, then add vegetables.
Boil 10 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars.
Process in boiling water for 10 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda and vanilla.
Stir in potato chips.
May add nuts, coconut or chocolate chips now.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Yield:
5 dozen.

title: pizzelle
directions: Melt the margarine, set aside to cool.
Beat the eggs; add sugar gradually, beating until smooth.
Add cooled, melted margarine and anise.
Sift the flour and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
(Dough should be sticky enough to drop off a spoon.) Preheat Pizzelle iron for about 4 minutes.
Drop dough by teaspoon onto a greased heated Pizzelle iron, press top down for about 35 to 45 seconds.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: fluffy 2-step cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix: Philadelphia Cream Cheese and sugar with electric mixer until well blended.
Gently stir in cool whip.
Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with cherry pie filling. Makes 8 servings.

title: creme brulee(thanksgiving dinner - mallory farms)
directions: Beat yolks till thick and lemon colored; gradually add white sugar.
Scald cream; pour slowly over yolks, stirring constantly. Add vanilla.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole; place in pan of hot water.
Bake 350 degrees for 1 hour or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Chill thoroughly.
When ready to serve, sprinkle top of casserole with sifted brown sugar, 1/2 inch deep. Place under broiler, leaving door open, to caramelize sugar to form crust.
Watch carefully as it burns quickly.
Surround with peach or pear halves, drained.
Serves 10.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate chip walnut muffins
directions: Mix together sugars, oil, eggs, milk, flour, chips and walnuts.
Spoon batter into muffin tins.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry-cheese coffeecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and margarine in large bowl until fluffy.
Add half of the flour, the eggs, milk, baking powder, baking soda, vanilla and salt.
Beat 2 minutes until well blended. Add remaining flour on low speed.

title: marty's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a large casserole dish.
Be sure meat is patted down firmly and flat on the top. Take a spoon and move the edges of the meat away from the sides of the dish (this will allow grease to escape from meat while it is baking).
Spread ketchup or barbecue sauce on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours covered.
Uncover and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Mix well by hand and pour into well greased 1-pound coffee cans. Bake at 300 degrees for 70 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread mix.
Cool and crumble. Add rest of ingredients.
Fold in salad dressing.
Chill.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Sift together flour, soda, bakewell cream and salt.
Mix oil and milk, then add to dry ingredients.
Pat out on floured board. Cut out biscuits and bake at 450° until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a large pot, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add water then broccoli, bouillon and worcestershire sauce.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened and broccoli is tender.
Add cheese and half & half. Cook and stir until cheese melts and soup is hot.
(Do not boil.)

title: crumb coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients until batter is smooth.
Grease and flour a large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out and cool, while making the crumbs.

title: wash day soup
directions: Put navy beans in a big pot of salted water to soak overnight. Put on the same time you do your wash water, about six in the morning, with the bacon or ham.
Let cook, uncovered, on low burner.
Check between loads of wash.
Add chopped onion at eight when you are bluing the overalls.
At nine have a quick cup of coffee and dump 1/2 a cup in the beans.
Add chopped carrots at bleach time (about 11:00).
Serve at noon over rice with soda crackers.

title: blender slaw
directions: Cut vegetables in 1-inch pieces.
Fill blender container half full.
Add water to within 1-inch of top.
Cover and whirl 2 seconds (no longer).
Drain vegetables well in colander; place in bowl.
Repeat process, reusing water until all vegetables are blended.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Combine first five ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for five minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Let cool just a little and mix with other ingredients in order given.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese. Bake in long Pyrex dish at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut 2 or 3 (1 1/2-inch) slices off the end of a pound of bacon.
Separate pieces and fry in a large cooking pot.
If there's not enough fat, add margarine.
Put in cold popcorn and shake until bacon bits are on the top.
Cover and wait until popping starts.
Shake until popping stops.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix and heat the first 5 ingredients.
Add chicken.
Beginning with tortillas, layer alternately tortillas, chicken and soup mixture; until all ingredients are used up.

title: chocolate candy bar dessert
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and 1/4 cup of sugar and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press firmly on bottom of pan.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar in medium bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle chopped candy bars over cream cheese layer.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Pour over chopped candy bar layer.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Garnish with additional chopped candy bars, if desired.
Cut into squares.
Keep refrigerated.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix. Roll into balls. Bake on greased cookie sheet for about 15 minutes in preheated oven to 325°.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: southern corn(corn pudding)
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in slow oven at 325° until firm in center, about 50 minutes.

title: crispy oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Rinse chicken and pat dry. Combine oil, salt, pepper, ginger, garlic and paprika in a small bowl. Place cereal in a pie plate or on a piece of foil. Brush each piece of chicken on both sides with oil mixture, then dip in cereal crumbs, pressing lightly to get an even coating on all sides. Place on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is golden brown and tender. Timing will vary according to the thickness of the chicken pieces.

title: white chili
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Mix all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover for 2 hours, stirring often.
Add chicken and cover for 1 hour.
Spread cheese and put chili on top of tortilla chips and add cheese.

title: quick blackberry pie
directions: Mix well.
Pat in greased pan and then put blackberries on top. Then put butter around on top.
Then bake.
Test to see when done.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine.
Stir in sugar, cocoa, nuts and vanilla.

title: janice's squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in salted water until squash is tender. Drain and mash.
Add eggs, butter, crumbled bacon and drippings. Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry bavarian cream
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving syrup.
Pour boiling water over gelatin and dissolve.
Add enough cold water to reserved syrup to measure 2 cups.
Stir into dissolved gelatin.
Chill until almost set.
In chilled bowl, prepare Dream Whip.
Beat gelatin until foamy.
Fold gelatin and strawberries into whipped cream.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold; if desired, garnish with whipped cream and strawberries.

title: "legal catsup"
directions: Combine tomato juice and vinegar.
Add garlic and sweetener, a little at a time, until flavor is right for you.
Use as a substitute for commercial catsup.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in casserole dish.
Lay pork chops on top. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Mix well and pour over first layer.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Mix together flour, oats, salt, baking powder and soda.
Place small amounts in blender and process until mixture turns into powder.
Mix butter-egg mixture with flour mixture until just blended.
Add chocolate pieces, milk chocolate and chopped nuts.

title: herbed fish fillets
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine corn meal and seasonings.
Dip fish in combined egg and milk.
Coat with corn meal mixture. Place in 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Drizzle with margarine. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges, if desired.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and then add mayonnaise to taste.

title: slices of lemon pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions for two-crust pie using 9 inch pie pan.
Do not use 8 inch pie pan. Heat oven to 400°.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Stir brown sugar, Karo syrup, salt and oleo in pan.
Stir over heat until mixture boils.
Let boil for 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over 6 quarts of popped corn (do not use hot air popper).
Stir until well coated.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In electric mixer, combine sugar, margarine and eggs. Add bananas and vanilla.
Add flour and soda. Add sour milk and pecans. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Wrap in foil when cool and allow to ripen 24 hours before eating.
Slices well when frozen.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Dissolve these layers with 1/2 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water and stir in 1/3 cup Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk.

title: jello salad
directions: Fix first layer of Jell-O (red or green).
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wait until jelled, then drain juice from pineapple and heat. Dissolve 15 marshmallows in juice, also lemon Jell-O.
Set aside. Mix rest of pineapple, cream cheese and salad dressing.
Mix all together and pour over Jell-O.
Let set, then mix the other Jell-O and put on top.

title: party rye
directions: Brown sausage and ground meat.
Add cheese (cut into pieces). Add approximately four tablespoons salsa.
Cool.
Spread on party rye and freeze on cookie sheets.
When frozen, transfer to Baggies and store in freezer.
To heat, put in 350° oven until slightly brown and serve hot.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli and swiss
directions: Cook broccoli, covered in a small amount of boiling water 10 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, butter and flour in container of an electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Set aside.
