Combine broccoli, corn and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Stir in cottage cheese mixture. Spoon into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle bacon on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well and
bake
at	325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until brown.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together; do not boil. Cream together the sugar and butter. Add flour alternately with milk, then add vanilla, cinnamon and nuts.
Put syrup in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add batter by spoonfuls to syrup.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
(Test with toothpick.)
Serve upside down.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Bring the sugar, chocolate and margarine to a boil.
Add the vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a bowl, mix the cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter together.
Fold in the topping.
Pour the mixture into the pie shells and chill several hours.
Yield:
2 pies.

title: mushroom, brown rice skillet
directions: Saute celery, onion and garlic in oleo for 5 minutes or until celery is crispy and tender.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Stir to dissolve bouillon.
Cover and steam over low heat, without stirring, for 50 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a very large container.
Use 1/3 cup of mix per 1 cup of boiling water.
Enjoy!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese until smooth; set aside.
Add finely chopped green onions (including tops).
Stir in cream cheese.
Wash dried beef to remove excess salt.

title: praline strips
directions: Spread crackers on greased cookie sheet, covering bottom.
Mix sugar, butter and nuts.
Spread on graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool for 10 to 12 minutes before serving.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add molasses and egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Roll in balls about the size of a small walnut; roll balls in granulated sugar.
Place on a cookie sheet, spaced about 1-inch apart and bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Yield:
4 dozen.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls flat on a greased baking sheet.
Let cool thoroughly.
Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix together.
Spread on cooled crescent roll dough.
Top with finely chopped vegetables.
Cut into bars.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter until the consistency of whipped cream.
Add sugar, one cup at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in sour cream.
Sift flour, soda and salt together 3 times; add 1/2 cup at a time to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring.
Pour into greased and lined (with wax paper) tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: two cheese baked chicken
directions: Spray your pan with Pam.
Wash chicken.
Mix oil and garlic powder together.
Dip chicken in oil mixture.
Mix other items together.
Coat chicken.
Place in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 3 greased loaf pans or one greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes (longer for tube pan).

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Fold in half of fruit.
Decorate with other half of fruit.
Ready to serve in 5 minutes or immediately.
Serves 10.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant, coat with flour and fry until brown. In oblong baking dish, place a layer of fried eggplant, hamburger, onion and cheese. Keep layering those things until used up. Mix soup, water and milk together and pour over all. Bake 1 hour at 425°.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Sprinkle rice evenly. Place lightly salted and peppered chicken on rice. Evenly spread soups and water on chicken. Sprinkle onion soup mix on chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: camper's casserole
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven. Brown 1-inch cubes of meat.
Stir in other ingredients. Simmer and cook 10 minutes.
Mix biscuit mix and water. Drop on stew.
Add oregano and paprika.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes or until dumplings are done.

title: almond bark crunchies
directions: Heat and melt bark in 200° oven (if your oven has the warm temperature, use that).
Watch carefully; burns easy.
When melted, blend mixture of remaining ingredients into bark.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Chill.
Makes about 100 according to size.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain and combine remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted butter, vanilla, lemon juice and pineapple.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Stir in oatmeal.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Set aside.

title: orange pork chops
directions: In electric frying pan, on medium-high heat, brown pork chops in oil on both sides.
To drippings, add onions; cook until brown. Return chops to pan; stir in sherry, soy sauce and marmalade. Heat to boiling; reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover; cook for 30 minutes.
Remove cover; increase heat to medium and cook until liquids are evaporated.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Combine oleo, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Mix well. Add crushed vanilla wafers, coconut and pecans. Mix well and bake in a bundt pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 250 degrees.

title: plain tea cakes
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add 1 cup of flour, then vanilla, then rest of flour; mix well.
Knead on floured surface.
Roll out thin.
Cut and bake at 325° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool a few minutes before removing from pan.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain and put in a 2-quart casserole, greased. Melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.

Remove from heat and add milk gradually. Cook onion and cheese and stir until cheese begins to melt. Pour over macaroni. Sprinkle with bread crumbs mixed with melted butter. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown hamburger; add chopped onion and chopped celery.
Mix all ingredients together and cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: The day before, drain juice from all fruit (oranges, pineapple and fruit cocktail).
Combine fruit, coconut, marshmallows and pecans.
Fold in sour cream.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with cherries before serving.

title: atomic salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in bottom of large salad bowl. Taste; it should be spicy.
Extra dry mustard will be of help. Put lettuce and spinach on top.
Do not toss.
When ready to serve, put tomatoes and croutons in and toss.

title: whipped fruit passion
directions: In a large bowl, pour water over gelatin; mix well and chill in refrigerator until slightly thickened. In a separate bowl, whip cream until fluffy. Fold in cream cheese and mix until well blended. Remove gelatin from refrigerator and add pecans, cherries and pineapple; mix well. Fold in whipped cream mixture. Pour into large serving dish and chill.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and syrup.
Add the peanut butter. Mix with the cereal.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate chips. Spread over top. Cut before too hard.

title: chocolate chip butterscotch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Combine flour and soda in a medium bowl; mix well with wire whisk. Set aside.
In a
large bowl, use an electric mixer to blend the sugar and butter.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until light and smooth. Scrape down sides of bowl, then add the flour mixture, pecans and chocolate chips.
Blend at low speed until just combined.
Do not overmix.
Place batter in pan.
Level evenly.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.
Yields 16 bars.

title: jalapeno chicken
directions: Remove stems and seed from chilies (reserve 1 for garnish). In 10-inch skillet in salad oil, cook chilies, onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in cumin and cook 1 minute.
Stir in soup, salt, spinach and break up spinach with fork.
Cover and simmer until spinach is cooked.
Stir in chicken and sour cream and heat through.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Blend sugars, eggs and butter until creamy.
Add pinto beans and blend well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for an additional 25 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: minute meat loaves(295 calories per serving)
directions: About 30 minutes before serving:
Preheat oven to 400°. Combine all ingredients, but olives.
Spoon mixture into 12 ungreased 3-inch cupcake cups.
Lightly press to shape.
Top each with olive half.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until well done.
Makes 12 individual loaves or 6 servings.

title: baked clams
directions: Prepare clams by soaking in cold, salted water for at least a few hours; this will take away fishy taste.
If you sprinkle 1 tablespoon of cornmeal over the top, the clams will eat it, expelling any sand and grit.
The clams will also be plump from their meal.
Shuck the clams and drain the juices.
Remove one shell and loosen the meat from the remaining shell.
Place in 1 layer in a baking dish.

title: sex-in-a-pan
directions: Mix the flour, pecans and butter, spread the mix in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 15-20 minutes until golden brown.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip, when the base has cooled pour this over the top.
Next, mix the vanilla pudding with 2 1/2 cups of milk and pour over the cheese mixture.
Mix the chocolate pudding with the remaining 2 1/2 cups of milk and pour over the top of the vanilla pudding.
Serve with an extra layer of Cool Whip and a sprinkling of chopped nuts.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix sugar and Milnot; place over medium heat.
Add butter or margarine; stir slowly until melted.
Continue stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Add entire bag of miniature marshmallows; stir constantly until melted and the mixture comes to a boil again.
Continue to stir and cook until the mixture turns a rich caramel color (approximately 10 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips; stir until dissolved and fudge starts to thicken.
Mix in vanilla, then pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Allow to set completely before cutting.
Cut into squares.
Makes approximately 5 pounds.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as package label directs and drain.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer mixture 1 minute. Remove from heat.

title: veiled maiden
directions: Amounts depend on number of servings.

title: diabetic cookie
directions: Boil water, shortening, raisins, nutmeg and cinnamon together for 3 minutes.
Let cool, then beat in eggs, one at a time. Dissolve salt, soda and sweetening agent in water and add to egg mixture.
Blend in flour sifted with baking powder.
Drop from a spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: golden onion rings
directions: Cut onions into 1/4-inch thick slices; separate into rings. Beat together rest of ingredients until flour is well moistened, then coat onion rings with batter.
Fry a few at a time in deep hot fat or oil at 375°, stirring once to separate rings.
When onions are golden, drain on paper towel.
Just before serving, sprinkle with salt.

title: chicken continental
directions: Dilute soup with 1 can water.
Place rice in 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour diluted soup over the rice.
Sprinkle with grated onion. Add chicken.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until chicken is done. May add moisture if needed.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: broccoli and corn
directions: Mix and put in casserole.
Top with 1/4 cup cracker crumbs mixed with 1 1/2 tablespoons melted oleo or buttered bread crumbs. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumbers in dill sauce
directions: Stir the sour cream (or yogurt), vinegar, sugar, dill weed, salt and pepper together.
Add cucumber and onion.
Toss to coat cucumber with sauce.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: no sugar drop cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add bran flakes, nuts and raisins.
Set aside.
Beat egg and add remaining ingredients. Stir in flour mixture; mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt and boil, stirring occasionally, until syrup is very thick (at least 20 minutes).
Add margarine and slowly stir in milk.
Stir constantly.
Cook rapidly to firm ball stage.
Add vanilla and pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool slightly, then cut or break into bite size pieces.
Wrap these in wax paper.
Makes about 100 pieces.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper together.
Then layer potatoes, onion, butter, paprika (sprinkle), cheese and soup.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour (covered).
Bake 15 minutes (uncovered).

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream oleo and brown sugar.
Add cream cheese to this then add sifted dry ingredients.
Roll in ball and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pizza pasta
directions: Combine sausage, onion, bell pepper and mushrooms in large skillet.
Cook until sausage is fully cooked.
Drain any excess grease.
Add tomatoes, pizza sauce, and water.
Cook over low heat for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese, olives and cooked pasta.
Continue to cook over low heat until cheese melts. When serving, top with a sprinkling of Parmesan.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and let set overnight.
Add remaining ingredients to cranberry mixture.
Mix together and let set a couple of hours before serving.

title: chicken and beef kabobs
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce, lemon juice, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, seasoned salt, garlic and tarragon; blend.
Add chicken and beef.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Place chicken, beef, mushrooms, carrots, onion and peppers alternately on skewers. Grill, basting with remaining sauce and turning occasionally until brown (approximately 8 to 10 minutes).
Serves 4.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: vanilla rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix.
In a saucepan, add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg over pudding.

title: fig preserves cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, sugar and spices.
Add oil and beat well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add figs, nuts and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased sheet pan and bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: tuna melt
directions: Spread tuna fish on a slice of bread.
Cover with a slice of tomato and a slice of cheese.
Bake in a 300° oven until cheese is melted and the bottom of the bread is lightly toasted.

title: beefed up beans
directions: In large saucepan, combine beans, 1/2 c. water, catsup, mustard, soy sauce, and Worcestershire sauce; add frozen meat mixture. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve in bowls with crackers. Makes 4-5 servings.

title: grandma's bread pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Grease small baking dish.
Bread crumbs should be dry but not stale, crusts removed.
Add butter to crumbs.
Add scalded milk and let stand until slightly cooled.
Add salt, sugar and beaten eggs.
Add flavoring and turn into greased pan or individual custard cups.
Set in pan of hot water and bake at 350° until firm, about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Then shape into balls. Set in refrigerator for a few minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip each ball in chocolate and put on wax paper.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by spoon to ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 minutes at 375°.

title: baking powder dumplings
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco with knife until crumbly.
Add liquid ingredients.
Mix until a thick batter is obtained.
Drop by 1 tablespoon spoonfuls into boiling soup or stew.
Cover tightly.
Cook about 10 to 12 minutes until dumplings rise.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add sifted flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla.
Last add hot milk with butter melted in it.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: angel food pineapple
directions: Mix dry pudding and Jell-O together.
Mix this with 1 cup pineapple juice.
Set aside.
Heat 3 cups milk.
Bring almost to a boil.
Add pudding and Jell-O.
Let boil for about 5 minutes. Cool to lukewarm.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and soda.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix flour, butter and chopped nuts together.
Press in bottom of pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Spread over cooled crust. Spread cherry pie filling on top and chill.

title: corn stuffing balls
directions: Heat oleo with water until oleo melts.
Stir into stuffing mix.
Add corn (drained) and parsley.
Then stir in eggs.
Shape in balls, pressing together.
Add a little more water, if necessary.
Arrange in buttered shallow baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate.
About 1 hour before baking, remove from refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, in hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes or until heated and lightly browned.
Makes 20 to 22 balls.

title: graham squares
directions: On a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam, place graham cracker squares to cover bottom.
Sprinkle sliced almonds over graham squares.
Melt butter; mix with brown sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes in microwave.
Spread mixture on top of graham crackers and almonds.
Cook in oven for 7 minutes on top rack.
When done, remove squares and place on wax paper lightly sprayed with Pam. Let cool.
Will keep very well frozen.

title: lemon luscious pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add butter, lemon juice and beaten egg yolks.
Stir in milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Cool.
Fold in sour cream. Chill at least 2 hours.
May be topped with whipped cream.

title: saunders frosting
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Slowly add sugar. Beat well. Scald milk and pour over egg mixture, then cool about 20 minutes. Add Crisco and oleo, beat well until fluffy. Add vanilla. Be sure to use room temperature oleo. Takes a long time to thicken. Do not mix in plastic bowl.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook meat, onions, chili powder, garlic and salt until brown. Add enchilada sauce, canned milk, green chilies and soup.
Line greased pan with tortillas.
Add layer of cheese, layer of sauce and repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: beef mushroom noodle soup
directions: Chop mushrooms fine. Add chopped onions and pepper.
Cook in pan with butter until tender, about 5 minutes.
Brown ground beef. Add the water and bring to a boil, letting it simmer for about 40 minutes, adding the noodles, spices and mushroom juice for the last 15 minutes of cooking. Serves a large group.

title: lucy's heavenly hash
directions: Stir all ingredients and place in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Stir again before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Cream rest.
Add dry ingredients. Bake for 1 hour 10 minutes in loaf pan at 350°.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Pour water and alum over cukes.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain. Wash well.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil, stirring.
Pour over pickles.
Reheat syrup every day for 3 days.
Ready to eat. Seal in sterilized jars; seal lids.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add basil and diced chicken.
Heat thoroughly. Taste and add seasoning as desired.

title: yummy breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 2 quart casserole dish.
Layer the sausage and 1 cup of
cheese
in
the
bottom
of
dish.
In medium bowl, combine the
eggs, grits, muffin mix, milk and butter and pour over the sausage
and cheese.
Top with the remaining cheese. At this point, uncooked mixture may be refrigerated overnight, if desired. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: Combine cooked rotelle, Italian dressing, seasoning and an assortment of chopped vegetables or pepperoni and cheese. Refrigerate.
Great for cookouts.

title: corn and peas salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Cool 5 minutes.
Combine corn and remaining ingredients in a bowl; stir in vinegar mixture. Cover and chill at least 8 hours, stirring occasionally.
To serve, use a slotted spoon.
Makes 8 servings.

title: date and pecan candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix the sugar and milk together.
Bring to a boil. Add cherries and dates.
Continue to cook slowly until a firm ball is formed when a small amount of the candy is dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Set the pan in a larger pan of cold water until mixture is almost cold. Beat until creamy and thick.
Add pecans.
Spoon the thick mixture onto a clean, slightly damp cloth.
Form into a long roll, approximately 1 1/2 to 2 inches in diameter.
With the mixture still wrapped in the cloth, refrigerate until firm enough to slice.

title: cherry cake cobbler
directions: Prepare cake batter as directed and pour evenly into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: triple good bar
directions: Heat oven to
Grease
a	13 x 9-inch baking pan. In saucepan, combine
the
first
ingredients.
Cook
over medium heat, stirring
constantly,
until	mix begins to boil. Set aside. Beat
margarine,

and vanilla until fluffy. Add remaining ingredients
and
blend.
Press
all
but 2 cups into a greased pan, then cover with raisin mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining oat mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Combine cookies and 1/4 cup butter.
Press into bottom of cake pan.
Put softened ice cream on cookie mixture and freeze.
Boil chocolate, butter, sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook until thick. Cool and add vanilla.
Spread on ice cream.
Freeze.
Put Cool Whip and nuts on top of chocolate and freeze.
Enjoy.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles for about 8 minutes.
Drain and mix with next 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle bread crumbs or potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: toad in a hole(breakfast)
directions: Cut center of bread out with end of a glass or round cookie cutter.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Add bread (both pieces).
Add egg to the center of cut bread.
Flip egg as desired.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Mix together bread crumbs, garlic salt, onion salt, Accent, Lawry's seasoning and Parmesan cheese.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Dip chicken in butter, then into mixture to coat.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti, not quite done.
Set aside.
In large heavy saucepan, melt shortening; add chopped onions and cook until tender.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add soup, tomatoes, mushroom with liquid, pimentos, chili powder, salt, sugar and pepper.
Add drained spaghetti.
Simmer on low 30 minutes.
Watch closely so it doesn't burn.
Better if sits awhile.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: okra fritters
directions: *Two cups frozen, sliced okra, thawed, may be substituted for sliced fresh okra.

title: no cook tomato basil sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Toss your favorite hot pasta with sauce, coating it evenly, and serve immediately.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Remove one half hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for one hour, using a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cherry nut congealed salad
directions: Use 1/4 cup of water to dissolve Knox gelatine and combine balance of water with cherries, juice, sugar and jello.
Heat mixture until jello and sugar dissolve; add gelatin mixture and nuts and pour into 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan and chill for several hours.
Serve in squares with Dream Whip or whipped cream cheese if desired.

title: green bay packer stew
directions: Add all ingredients in casserole.
Cover and bake at 250° for 4 hours.
May use consomme if you omit sugar and tomato juice.
It is a good, busy day meal.
This used to be called Paul Hornung stew.

title: jamaica cake
directions: Stir all together, either by hand or mixer.
Place in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350° (time approximate).
Test for doneness.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch in top of double boiler or microwave.
Add nuts and noodles.
Mix and drop on waxed paper on cookie sheet. Refrigerate to harden.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt Hershey bars.
Cream oleo with sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to sugar mixture alternately with flour and salt.
Add chocolate syrup, vanilla, melted Hershey bars and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: brazos de la reina
directions: Simmer 1 cup milk over low heat.
Stir until milk has evaporated to 1/2 its original quantity.
Add enough sugar to sweeten.
Beat egg yolks in a mixing bowl.
Add to egg yolks by spoonfuls, beating after each addition, the thickened milk.
When most of the milk has been added to the egg yolks, pour the mixture of milk and egg yolks to the rest of the milk in a saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring constantly to avoid curdling.
Add cashew nuts and continue cooking in low heat until of paste consistency.
Shape into a loaf.
Beat egg whites until it stands in peaks.
Add 1 cup sugar, little by little, beating mixture continuously.
Flavor with vanilla.
Set aside.
Brush loaf generously with butter, then top with 1/2 of the meringue, forced through a cake decorator tube.
Brown in slow oven about 325° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Lay upside-down on pan lined with buttered paper. Brush top with butter and cover with remaining meringue.
Brown in oven the same way as the other side.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together. Put in freezer and chill until firm. Use 8 x 8 glass Pyrex dish.

title: cinnamon pudding cake
directions: Mix first 3 items together and let come to a boil.
Set aside.
Cream the next 7 items together.
Mix with first ingredients.
(If too stiff, add small amount milk.)
Pour into pan.
Pour syrup mixture on top.
Do not mix.
Cover with nuts. Cook at 350° until done.

title: 30 day friendship cake
directions: Pour ingredients into a glass jar.
Cover and allow to ferment for 2 weeks; do not refrigerate.
Stir daily until sugar is dissolved.

title: quiche
directions: Beat eggs, half and half, salt and pepper together for 1 minute.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Cook spinach and drain.

title: pie crusts
directions: Crumb together flour, Crisco, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add egg, water and vinegar.
Mix and roll out onto floured surface.
Makes approximately 5 crusts.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Stir in onions. Spread over ham slices. Roll up jelly roll style. Chill for at least an hour. Before serving, cut into 1-inch pieces. Yield: 40 appetizers.

title: quick bread or mayonnaise biscuits(serving size: 6)
directions: Mix ingredients and put into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: red lobsters cheddar bay biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees.
Mix Bisquick, milk, and cheese until a soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cooking sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes until golden brown.
Mix butter and garlic powder.
rush mixture over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.

title: herb sour cream bread
directions: Pour warm water into a large, warm bowl; sprinkle with yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add sour cream, margarine, sugar, salt, marjoram, oregano, thyme and eggs.
Beat in 3 cups of flour until well blended, about one minute.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk (about 50 minutes).
Stir down dough and turn into 2 greased 1-quart casserole dishes.
Cover; let rise until doubled in bulk (about 50 minutes).
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes or until done.
Remove from casserole dishes and cool on wire racks.

title: chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, sugar and salt. Cut off broccoli flowerets and reserve for future use.
Peel and shred stems.
Chop apple into 1/2-inch pieces (do not peel).
Toss apple, broccoli and raisins with the dressing.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Stir all together in bowl with 1 cup sour cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and butter in a large skillet.
Drain off excess butter and place into a large casserole dish.
Add salt, pepper, sour cream, soup and shredded cheese; mix well.
Add 1 cup of bread crumbs to mixture to thicken.
Top casserole with other cup of bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Slice bologna thin.
Insert cheese slice and roll up.
Wrap slice of bacon around and secure with toothpick.
Bake until cheese is melted, then brush with 2 tablespoons orange marmalade jelly.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, sugar, egg, cocoa, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Heat oven to 400°; drop by teaspoon (or larger) 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook. Immediately remove from baking sheet.
Cool.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and soda.
Add the remaining ingredients. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked ham
directions: Slice ham and place in baking dish.
Cover with RC and cover with lid.
Bake at 350° until heated thoroughly.
May add brown sugar for extra sweetness.

title: roasted potatoes parmesan
directions: Pierce potatoes several times with fork.
Arrange in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Bake in 375° oven until tender (about 1 hour).
If desired, you may cover and refrigerate for next day serving.

title: no fry potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes into wedges.
Mix with olive oil.
Place on baking sheet and sprinkle with Cajun spice to taste.
Bake for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Bring to boil.
Stir.
Lower heat to simmer and cook for 30 minutes.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal at once.
Makes 5 pints.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Toast almonds and sesame seed in oven 5 to 6 minutes until golden brown or microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes.
In large bowl, combine cabbage and onion.
In small bowl combine seasoning packet from noodles, vinegar, oil, sugar and pepper; blend well.
Pour dressing over salad.
Toss to coat.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: shrimp royal
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Add shrimp, mushrooms and green pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are pink.
Add lemon peel and sherry, stirring to mix. Serve with rice or toast squares and lemon wedges.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie plate 3/4 full with sliced apples.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and cinnamon.
Mix margarine, flour, sugar and egg. Spread over apples.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Whip cream cheese, sour cream and garlic with mashed potatoes. Pour into greased baking dish and sprinkle chives on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tangy pizza sauce
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and spread on pizza crust or bread.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix lemonade with 1/2 the water the can calls for.
Add sherbet and 7-Up.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Make cake per directions on box.
Cool for 1/2 hour.
Mix 1 1/2 cups hot water and orange Jell-O powder.
Poke holes in cake with toothpick.
Pour orange Jell-O over cake.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Mix pudding with cold milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Ice cake with this mixture.
Put Mandarin orange slices on top.

title: pink pig cake
directions: Mix
together
cake
mix, eggs, oil and mandarin oranges (juice and all); bake in loaf pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool
and
top
with crushed pineapple and vanilla instant pudding.
Mix well and fold in Cool Whip.

title: sunshine jello
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water and juice from pineapple and water makes 2 cups cold water.
Spoon pineapple into Jell-O and mix.
While still warm, put on 1 layer of marshmallows over Jell-O.
Let set.
Whip the cream until set.
Fold in mayonnaise and layer on top. Grate cheese fine and sprinkle lightly on top.

title: sweet and sour cocktail wieners or little smokies
directions: Mix and heat. Serve with toothpicks.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix 1 stick oleo and crumbs together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, 2 sticks oleo and sugar; beat for 15 minutes. Pour into crust.
Cut bananas and put on top.
Pour pineapple on top. Cover with whipped topping. Decorate with cherries and pecans.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs and a stick of margarine (melted) and pat down in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *(Example: cucumber, celery, mushrooms, green onion, broccoli, shredded carrots, etc., etc., etc.).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Take out stems and chop fine.
Add 1 envelope onion soup mix and grated cheese to stems.
Stuff in mushrooms.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Cover with foil for conventional oven or with glass lid for microwave.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or microwave on High 5 minutes.
Check and microwave 2 minutes, additionally, until tender.

title: layer salad
directions: Place lettuce leaves in your bowl and layer the ingredients in the order given.
Sprinkle the cheese and bacon bits on top of the salad.

title: classic family meat loaf
directions: In
a large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup of the soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion, Worcestershire sauce, egg and pepper.
In a 12 x 8-inch baking pan, firmly shape meat into an 8 x 4-inch loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done. Spoon off fat, reserving 1 to 2 tablespoons drippings.
In 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat remaining soup, water and reserved drippings to boiling, stirring occasionally. Serve sauce with meat loaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: simple salami
directions: Mix all ingredients except water. Add water and mix again. Shape into 2 rolls. Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake unwrapped in baking dish 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Can be baked in loaf pan. Rewrap to store. Freezes good.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Cook white sugar and Karo over low heat; stir continuously. Bring just to a boil.
Remove from fire.
Stir in peanut butter. Add the Rice Krispies; mix well.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch buttered pan.
Melt chocolate bits and butterscotch bits and spread over the top.
Cut in squares after cooked.

title: salmon burger
directions: Drain salmon; flake.
Combine ingredients; mix well.
Form into 4 or 5 patties.
Pan-fry in small amount of oil until lightly browned on both sides.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.
Top with favorite condiments.

title: irish tea scones
directions: Knead dough out on floured surface.
Roll dough out to about 1/2-inch.
Cut out scones with the rim of a drinking glass and place on a floured pan.
Bake in a 450° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lime dessert
directions: Make jello.
While still liquid, combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: spiral cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine 1/4 cup milk, sugar, salt and 3 tablespoons butter in a saucepan.
Heat until butter melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°. Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in milk mixture, 1 1/2 cups flour and eggs.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in remaining 3/4 cup flour.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 minutes).
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, 1 hour (dough will not quite double in bulk).
Punch dough down.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Roll dough into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Spread with 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle mixture over rectangle.
Sprinkle with raisins, if desired.
Roll dough jelly roll fashion, starting at long side.
Pinch seam to seal (do not seal ends).
Cut roll into 1-inch slices.
Place slices, cut side down, in greased 8-inch square pan.
Brush tops with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Using a fork, gently lift center of rolls to form a peak.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, about 40 minutes.
(Rolls will not double in bulk.) Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons milk, stirring well.
Drizzle over warm rolls.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: chewy cakes
directions: Mix well.
Batter will be thick to work with.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or a little longer.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach; mix in beaten egg, cream cheese and onion powder to taste.
Pour in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt butter in large skillet. When butter foams, add cream. Simmer over medium heat about 2 minutes until slightly thickened. Season with salt and pepper. Fill a very large saucepan 2/3 full with salted water. Bring to boil. Add noodles. Cook, uncovered, until tender, but firm to the bite. Drain. Place in skillet with cream. Add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Toss noodles and sauce over medium heat until sauce coats noodles, 20 to 30 seconds. Serve with additional cheese, if desired. Serves 4 to 6.

title: frosted raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cranberry sauce, stirring with a wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in pineapple and wine and spoon into a lightly oiled 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: easy german chocolate cake(makes 2 layer cake)
directions: Cut wax paper to fit bottoms of two 9-inch round cake dishes. Place 1/4 cup butter in each lined dish.
Microwave, one dish at a time, at High 45 seconds to 1 1/4 minutes or until butter is melted and bubbly.
Mix 1/3 cup coconut and 1/3 cup pecans into butter in each dish.
Spread into an even layer.
Set dishes aside.
Place remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Blend at low speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Divide and spread batter into cake dishes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat potatoes, butter, milk, salt and sugar until fluffy. Fold in coconut and 1 cup marshmallows.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining marshmallows and nuts.
Bake at 350° until marshmallows are brown.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and zucchini.
Bake in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Saute chicken in butter until brown and then transfer to baking dish.
Saute the onions; add garlic (finely chopped).
Add sliced mushrooms.
Stir in white wine.
Thicken slightly with a small amount of cornstarch.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and place in 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: easy chicken and dressing
directions: Debone chicken; cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix with soups and broth.
Add stuffing and butter; mix well.
Bake in 10 x 13-inch pan 30 minutes at 350°.
Reduce baking time for moister chicken.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Chill for at least 1 hour and serve.

title: speedy summer gazpacho
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
May need to do in several batches.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into a large bowl or pitcher. Chill.
Serve with additional garnish, chopped cukes, chopped green onion and chopped tomatoes, if desired.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg yolks.
Put all dry ingredients in sifter; add to creamed mixture.
Alternately add milk and mix ingredients together.
Spoon on cookie sheet by teaspoon about an inch apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; salt and drain.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine other ingredients for sauce. Mix well.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian almond cookies
directions: Beat egg whites with fork until small bubbles form.
Set aside.
Blend sugar and almond paste until fluffy, fine and smooth.
(This will take a while.)
Add egg whites and blend until mixture is wet.
Shape into small balls with wet hands.
Roll in nuts.
(I use slivered almonds or pignolia (pine) nuts.)
Place on foil covered cookie sheet and bake for about 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cookies should be light golden brown.
Bake one tray at a time.
Do not remove from foil until cookies are cold.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables or chips.

title: no cook strawberry jam
directions: Put strawberries and Sure-Jell in a large bowl.
Stir and set aside 30 minutes.
Add white syrup and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Put in jars and freeze.
This is very good as ice cream topping.

title: pasta seafood salad
directions: Boil macaroni according to package directions.
Cut Crab Delight flakes in half.
Combine crab with remaining ingredients. Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: jello lemon cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Let it cool before adding to cake mix.
Mix oil with cake mix.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add Jell-O and flavoring; mix well with mixer.
Grease and flour Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in regular home oven.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy; add melted butter, flour, milk and sugar.
Beat well.
Add corn and mix by hand, then add salt and pepper as desired.
Pour in 8-inch square pan that is well-buttered.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is light brown in color.

title: yellow squash pickles
directions: Have 12 pint jars washed and sterilized.
Bring to a full boil; pack and seal.
Makes 12 pints.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all together; beat with mixer.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute onions and bell peppers over medium heat until they become limp.
Add chopped tomatoes and all remaining ingredients, except shrimp and rice.
Simmer just long enough to eliminate excess liquid, about 15 minutes.
Add the shrimp and continue cooking for a few minutes or until the shrimp are cooked.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: party sandwiches(can be made the day before and put in tight box.)
directions: Cream cheese, drain tuna and add (also, cut into small pieces).
Add onion, pickle and salad dressing.
Mix well.
Put on bread.
Cut into 1/4 pieces.
If for kids, don't trim crust.
If for adult party, trim edges.
Serve with chips and drinks.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup in a skillet.
Let cook until it hangs from a thread off a spoon; add peanuts.
Cook until syrup is light amber color.
Stir in butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda quickly.
Pour into greased pan and let cool.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Blend butter, Crisco and sugar and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flavoring with milk and add alternately with flour. Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream
oil,
sugar
and vanilla;
add eggs.
Make thick paste of	cocoa and food coloring and add to creamed mixture. Sift flour
and	salt
together	and alternate buttermilk and flour
to creamed mixture.
Bake in 9-inch pans 30 minutes at 350°.

title: date roll
directions: Boil sugar and milk to soft ball stage (235°).
Stir in dates and nuts.
Allow to cool.
Butter a sheet of foil and dust with powdered sugar.
Form the mix into a 1 1/2-inch roll and wrap in the prepared foil.
Chill until firm; slice with hot knife.

title: deluxe potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion until tender.
Add milk, bouillon and butter.
Mix sour cream and flour, add to soup and cook, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until done.
Peel, slice and arrange in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over sweet potatoes. Slice oranges thin, leaving peel and lay over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Baste 3 times during cooking in 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set in refrigerator for 24 hours. Place in jars.
Seal.
Makes 2 pints.

title: mom's rice pudding
directions: Bake at 375° for approximately 2 1/4 hours or until rice is done.
Stir several times during baking.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Beat in eggs. Add remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: ribbon jello
directions: Will also need a 9 x 13-inch dish, well oiled and chilled.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and set aside.
Brown hamburger and drain off fat.
Layer hamburger, sauce and cottage cheese together in a baking dish.
Put sauce in the bottom, then squash and then cheese.
Continue layering until all ingredients have been used. Bake for 1 hour at 425°.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add berries; stir until thick.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 in 8 x 8-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Spoon sour cream over.
Pour rest of jello mixture over; chill.

title: chocolate truffle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Place chocolate in a food processor and process with the sharp blade until chocolate is like coarse meal.
Add egg yolks, butter, sugar and extract and process until smooth.
In a large mixing bowl, combine egg whites, water and salt and beat until very stiff.
Fold chocolate mixture into egg whites and pour batter into a greased and lined 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 50 minutes.
Cool cake on a cake rack.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with water.
Add softened cream cheese, condensed milk and pineapple (including juice).
Add nuts and pour into mold.
Put into mold and refrigerate until congealed, about 8 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, butter or oil, then add mashed pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients (flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and cinnamon).
Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350°
for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rice with pine nuts
directions: Bring stock to a boil.
Add rice and 2 tablespoons of butter. Cover and simmer 20 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Heat remaining butter until slightly bubbly.
Add nuts and saute only until lightly browned.
Pour nuts and butter over rice.
Add raisins and fluff mixture with a fork.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no-fry french fries(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice potatoes in 1/4-inch ovals and then slice each oval lengthwise into matchsticks.
Coat baking sheet with 3 sprays of vegetable oil.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Beat the egg with the salt, sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Add the oil slowly, drop by drop, until half has been used.
Add the paprika or the pepper and add the rest of the oil.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces.
Mix rest of ingredients together; stir well.
Add cake pieces and mix gently.
Place in glass bowl and chill.

title: lemon lush
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Press into 8 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese in a bowl until fluffy.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust.

title: cheesy corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, cheese, chiles, onion, milk and eggs.
Combine cornmeal, garlic salt and soda.
Stir into corn mixture.
Grease large baking dish.
Pour mixture in and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Great with chili or barbecue.

title: shredded potato and ham pie
directions: In bowl, combine eggs, peas, ham, 1 cup cheese, milk and onion.
Set aside.
Combine shredded potatoes and 1/2 cup cheese. Press into bottom and sides of lightly greased pie plate.
Pour filling into potato lined pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until center is set.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: deer meat pot pie
directions: Brown deer meat in a large skillet.
Add mixed vegetables. In a bowl, make a gravy by adding the milk and flour together. Mix in bouillon cubes, salt and pepper.
(May need more or less milk and flour, depending on thickness.) Pour gravy over the browned meat and vegetables.
Heat until thickens.
Pour into a 10-inch pie crust.
Cover with pie crust top and bake at 375° until crust is golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: imly and khajur chutney(a sweet and sour chutney)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for another 15-20 minutes.
Cool and strain the mixture through a sieve.
You may also puree the cutney in a blender then strain it.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk; blend well. Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened. Reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Spread small amount on bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover with layer of Nilla wafers. Top with layer of sliced bananas. Pour about 1/3 of custard over bananas. Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard to make 3 layers of each, ending with custard. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff. Spoon on top of pudding. Cover entire surface. Bake at 425° until browned.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well. Put in jell jars and refrigerate.

title: five minute mexican dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and press into a Pyrex dish.
Pour 3/4 jar of salsa over cream cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over salsa. Microwave 5 minutes to melt cheeses.

title: banana bread
directions: Day Before Serving:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, with fork, mix first 5 ingredients.
With pastry blender or two knives, used scissor-fashion, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With fork, stir in bananas and orange juice, just until blended.
Spread batter evenly in pan.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix all together except chicken and onion soup.
Put chicken on top of mixture and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Seal casserole with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to instructions on box.
While cake is still warm, pierce with fork.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and liquid coconut well, then drizzle over warm cake.
Thaw 2 packages of frozen coconut.
Add this to one carton of Cool Whip and frost cake.
Seal and ripen overnight in refrigerator.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients into mixing bowl; mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until brown.

title: famous bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of water.
Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Mix and pour yeast mixture into flour.
Add beaten egg and mix.
Add enough flour to form a dough, but do not make too stiff.
Roll out rolls; cut into circles with cutter.
Dip each circle into melted butter, coating both sides. Fold over and place in pan, touching.
Let rise 1 1/4 hours.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Stir or cut in shortening until you have coarse texture.
Add buttermilk and knead.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss all ingredients except dressing.
Serve with dressing. Makes 6 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan.
Add 1/2 cup beef stock.
Let simmer a few minutes.
Place pork chops and juices from frypan into a casserole.
Add salt, pepper and thyme.
Pour 1 cup of beef stock over contents.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients like dough.
Mix together the next 3 ingredients; put this on crust.
Top with the pudding, mixed with the milk.

title: chili lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to the package direction; drain.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients, except English muffins.
Split muffins in half.
Spread with cheese mixture.
Cut into quarters. Broil on middle rack of oven for 6 minutes.
Cheese mixture will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.
This is a great after-school snack!

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish, assemble ingredients in layers (do not mix):
ground beef, 1 can of soup, Ranch Style beans, chopped onion, half of grated cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes, other can of soup and the rest of the grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brown hamburger stew
directions: I found him a laying in the road.

title: honey baked pork 'n beans
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Mix
all ingredients in 2 1/2 quart Pyrex bowl.
Lay bacon
on top of mixture and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours
until
bacon is completely cooked.
The longer it simmers the better it is!

title: cherry squares
directions: Blend with pastry blender; then add 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Put in cup and mix with fork; then add to pastry and mix lightly with fork.
Press 1/2 of mixture in cookie sheet.
Put in 2 cans of filling.
Sprinkle with rest of pastry.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: monkey balls
directions: Cut each biscuit into fours.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon together.
Roll each biscuit into balls.
Roll or shake balls in the sugar and cinnamon; mix.
Place in a greased tube pan.
Melt 1 stick of margarine; add 1/4 cup of sugar to the remaining mix. Bring to a boil.
Pour over balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let stand for 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: ripe cucumber pickles
directions: Cut into chunks.
Boil in water until clear and tender (do not overcook).
Dip out as they clear.

title: czechoslovakian bars
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat in flour. With floured hands, pat half of dough into well-greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread preserves over dough. Sprinkle nuts or coconut over preserves.
Pat remaining dough over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely, one hour or more in pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into small squares or bars.

title: sausage corn soup
directions: Cut up sausage and onion; brown together.
Add water, potatoes, corn, creamed corn and milk.
Heat clear through.

title: mud cake
directions: Cream the butter, cocoa and sugar.
Add in the eggs and vanilla.
Beat well then add flour, nuts and coconut.
Beat mixture for two more minutes.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. While hot, spread with jar of marshmallow cream.
Let cool and top with icing.

title: molded lime-pineapple salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Pour over jello, stirring until dissolved.
Combine softened cream cheese and mayonnaise, mixing until well blended.
Stir and gradually add jello, mixing until well blended.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Garnish with curly endive and frosted grapes.
Serves 12.

title: vegetable-tuna casserole
directions: Cook shell macaroni according to directions on package; drain. Add tuna, soup, onion, vegetables and seasonings; mix until combined.
Pour mixture into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: club pickles
directions: Drain and discard juice from pickles.
Cut into 3/4 inch thick slices and place in a two gallon crock.
(Do not use aluminum.) Pour sugar and spices over pickle slices. After 24 hours stir with wooden or stainless steel spoon.
Then stir 2 or 3 times daily. They are ready to eat after the third day.
May be left in crock (covered) or packed into four one-quart jars and sealed.

title: foolproof cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well. Roll dough onto foil or wax paper, making a log.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Slice 1/2-inch thick and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spiced french toast
directions: In a shallow dish, blend first 6 ingredients.
In a skillet, melt 2 tablespoons Crisco.
Dip both sides of bread in egg mixture. Place 2 to 3 slices in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until golden brown on both sides.
Repeat with remaining slices, adding remaining Crisco, if necessary.

title: pineapple-coconut chess pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, then add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour in pie shell.
Cook at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes.
Pie should be golden brown, and center of pie should barely shake when touched.

title: cornbread stuffin'
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a large saute pan.
Add the onion and celery and saute until soft, but not brown, approximately 5 minutes.
Stir in your cornbread and brown cubes and continue cooking until golden brown.
About another 10 minutes, add your seasonings and slowly stir in the stock until the stuffing reaches your preferred consistency.
Enough to stuff a 15 pound bird.

title: carrot-broccoli salad
directions: Mix together separate the salad dressing, dill weed and garlic salt.
Stir all together.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Crumble over top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fried cookies
directions: Mix soft butter and brown sugar; mix and add flour, powdered milk, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
Add wheat germ, raisins, egg and honey; mix with hands.
Sprinkle flour on clean table top; flour hands.
Shape pieces of dough into little balls. Roll in flour and flatten.

title: large shells
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
Gently toss with olive oil. Cover and set aside.
Mix spinach, garlic, onion, cheeses, parsley, egg, spices and seasonings.
Pour enough spaghetti sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan to sparingly cover bottom. Gently fill shells with spinach mixture, and place side by side in pan.
Spoon more sauce over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with more Mozzarella if desired, and bake 10 more minutes.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Melt in skillet margarine, then add celery, cabbage, tomatoes, green pepper, salt, sugar and onion.
Cover.
Cook over medium-low heat until done.

title: cranberry-sour cream ring
directions: Mash cranberry sauce with fork.
Dissolve plain gelatin in less than 1/4 cup cold water.
Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Combine the 2 gelatins; add cranberry sauce.
Add entire contents of pineapple can and nuts.
Put 1/2 of mixture in mold.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours, until firm.

title: stuffed eggs mexican-style
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks.
Mash yolks with onion, green pepper, chili powder, salt, Tabasco sauce, lemon juice and oil.
Stuff egg whites with egg-yolk mixture; garnish each egg with a shrimp and a tiny sprig of parsley.
Place on plate surrounded by fresh green lettuce; refrigerate until serving time.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook celery, onions and bell pepper in butter until tender. Add mushrooms and cook for a short time.
Add 2 cups stock and Worcestershire sauce.
Add soup, cheese and mayonnaise; stir well. Add chicken, spaghetti, salt and pepper.
Add more stock if it seems too dry.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 16 servings.

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs and salt to taste.
Add flour to make a stiff dough. Roll out very thin.
Cut with a noodle cutter or roll up the sheet of dough fairly tight and cut with a sharp knife.
Now unroll the little slices.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Coat chicken in flour.
In pan, melt the margarine and brown the chicken on both sides, 4 minutes per side.
Put in warm platter.

title: garlic herb cheese ball
directions: In a small bowl put all ingredients.
Mix well and form into a ball.
Wrap in Saran Wrap or waxed paper.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Store in airtight bag.

title: pork tenderloin and pea pods
directions: Freeze tenderloin as it slices easier.
Slice in rounds and pour soy sauce to cover; marinate a few hours.
Dip in flour and brown in small amount of cooking oil.
Add 1 to 2 cups of water mixed with about 1/4 flour and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add pea pods and chestnuts; cook a few minutes longer.
You may also add a little more soy sauce.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Season to taste with salad seasoning, then serve with any vegetables.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Beat in salt, sugar, flavoring, then boiling hot milk (heated with the butter in it) and flour sifted with baking powder.
Promptly pour into tube pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350° moderate oven.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix together with hand beater until smooth.
Refrigerate until chilled through.
In large casserole dish, layer lettuce, tomatoes, taco sauce, cream cheese/sour cream/taco mix mixture and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: polish zucchini
directions: Dice garlic, onions and kielbasa; saute in 1 tablespoon oil until onions are tender.
Add zucchini which has been thinly sliced.
Saute until zucchini is tender.
Add salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese and stir.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well. Beat egg yolks and add to the Cheddar and cream cheeses.
Add flour, margarine, onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Then add 1/4 cup of the Parmesan.
Add drained spinach and mix
thoroughly. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the spinach mixture. (Don't add whites until last minute.)
Spray casserole with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan over top and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fruit "crush" beverage
directions: Empty pineapple, grapefruit sections (do not drain) and mandarin oranges (drained) into blender.
Blend together.
Bring to boil 4 cups water and 1 cup sugar.
Combine the two and mix together.
Pour into Pyrex dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Cover with Saran Wrap; place in freezer.

title: cornmeal prune loaf with lemon glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Put margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, cornmeal, salt and baking powder.
Then sift together.
Add to first mixture and beat slowly until well mixed.
Add rum and beat until batter is smooth and well blended. Stir in prunes.
Pour into prepared pan and smooth top with spatula.
Bake about 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until tester comes out clean.
Remove from oven and immediately spread Lemon Glaze on top of loaf.
Let rise in pan about 5 to 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack to cool completely.
Store loaf well wrapped and freeze, if not to be used within 2 days.

title: lemon barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling in 3-quart pan.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered.
Stir occasionally for 10 minutes.
Serve hot over your favorite cooked meats or baste whatever you like to grill.
Can be used on all meats and seafood.
Cover and store in refrigerator for up to 1 week.
For longer storage, remove lemon slices and store in fridge up to 1 month.
Makes 6 cups.

title: dried beef appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese and add all ingredients to shredded dried beef.
Mix well.

title: curried chicken over rice
directions: Saute chicken in
tablespoon
margarine until brown. Remove chicken
to
bowl.
To
drippings,
add
tablespoon margarine, onions and garlic;	saute until brown.
Add 1/4 cup water.	Add curry powder and cook
for 2 minutes.
Add rest of water and tomato paste.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add chicken and simmer until chicken is
tender,
30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: perfect everytime meringue
directions: Let egg whites stand until room temperature.
Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar on high speed with electric mixer until just foamy.
(Overbeating at this stage may cause weeping.)
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until soft peaks form and all sugar has dissolved.
Add vanilla and beat until glossy peaks form. Spread on hot pie filling, sealing to edge.
Using spatula, swirl top of meringue decoratively.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pepper relish
directions: All measurements are after being chopped.
Sprinkle salt over chopped vegetables.
Let stand about 30 minutes.
Drain well.
Add vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Cook until thick. Put in jars and seal.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Into bottom of pan, put about 1 cup water and bring to boil. Add vegetables onto steamer in order given.
Add salt and pepper to season.
Cover and let steam for about 20 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Check to see if more water is needed about halfway through cooking time.

title: janet's cake
directions: Melt margarine and shortening.
Stir in cocoa and water; bring to a boil.
Stir flour and sugar together.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 15 1/2 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Spray casserole with Pam.
Put in good layer of crushed crackers and dot with margarine.
Mix soups, chicken, sour cream, onions and pepper. Pour over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pizza pork chops
directions: In a medium saucepan combine all ingredients except the pork chops and the cheese.
Bring the sauce to a low boil for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to simmer for an hour.
Place pork chops in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour sauce over the chops and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from the oven. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and serve.

title: carrot cheddar bake
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Place the carrots into 8 x 10-inch buttered baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the carrots.
Bake for 45 minutes or until hot and puffy.
Cut into squares to serve.
Makes about 4 to 6 servings.

title: peachy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and refrigerate.

title: praline-crusted cheesecake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and butter. Press into bottom and up sides of a greased 10-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cool on a wire rack. Sprinkle coarsely crumbled Pralines over crust.

title: cheese spam bake
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
Cool, peel, slice or dice in casserole.
Reserve 1 cup potato water.
Melt oleo and simmer onion in oleo.
Add flour, dry mustard, salt, pepper and paprika. Add the cup of potato water; mix well and add 1 cup milk.
Cook until it thickens.
Add cubed Spam and 1 cup diced cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Boil cabbage leaves in salted water for about 3 minutes; drain.
Combine egg, salt, onion, milk and 1/4 cup of the barbecue sauce; mix well.
Add beef, pork and rice; mix lightly.
Place 1/2 cup meat mixture in center of each cabbage leaf.
Fold sides and ends of leaves over meat mixture; secure with wooden picks.
Saute in butter in a skillet about 5 minutes, or until golden on both sides.
Add remaining barbecue sauce and the water.
Cover and cook 40 minutes, basting twice during cooking.
Remove cover and cook another 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: open-faced burger patties with onions
directions: You will need Pam spray.

title: fried cheese
directions: Dip cheese in egg.
Coat with crumbs.
Fry in deep hot oil at 350° for 1 to 2 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cebiche
directions: Blanch shrimp, scallops, squid and octopus.
Peel shrimp.
Cut fish into 1/2-inch cubes.
In glass or ceramic bowl, mix raw fish and other seafood with salt, onion, hot pepper and enough lemon juice to cover.
Stir.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir several times.
The lemon juice "cooks" the raw fish and pickles the onions.
Serve chilled on a bed of lettuce surrounded by slices of room temperature sweet potato.
This appetizer serves 8 or more.

title: hominy chili pot
directions: Drain hominy and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in oil.
Add ground beef and cook until lightly browned.
Drain excess fat from pan.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder, sugar and tomatoes.
Stir and allow to simmer 10 minutes.
Add hominy. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk lemon pound cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Mix milk and flavorings; set aside.
Cream Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beat after each addition until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff and carefully fold into mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Leave in pan for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto plate and cover.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion, pepper and rice in butter.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, covered.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Fry sausage, onion, celery and green pepper.
Add cream of mushroom soup, chicken noodle soup, water and rice.
Mix together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven or until it bubbles.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add can of undiluted mushroom soup and cheese.
Mix until cheese is melted, over low heat.
Mix with broccoli (thawed) and rice (cooked).

title: no name rice dish
directions: Cook rice in water until done.
Cube and fry the bacon crisp. Cook onions, bell peppers and carrots. Drain and add mushrooms. Scramble the eggs and add to the vegetables. Add the cooked rice to this and mix well.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and green onions in butter.
Add soup and heat. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish. Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix and put in a loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crunch-top potatoes
directions: Melt butter in jelly roll pan in moderate oven (375°).
Add single layer of potatoes; turn once in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over.
Bake 1/2 hour or until done and tops are crisp.
Serve hot.

title: hot chocolate(really good)
directions: Mix this all together and place into a jar that has a tight lid on it. Best to store it in the refrigerator or in a cool place.
Use only 1/3 cup of this mixture to 1 cup hot water. Mix and drink hot.
Marshmallows on top is excellent or a dab of whipped topping.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together using just enough milk for right consistency.
Drop by spoonfuls into small, greased muffin pans. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: pound cake klemkowski
directions: * Buttermilk can be made with 1 cup milk and 1 tablespoon vinegar; let stand.

title: snowflakes
directions: Fold tortillas into fourths.
Cut designs from folded edges with scissors.
Unfold.
Fry one tortillas at a time until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve immediately.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients and form into 1 inch balls. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Great for parties.

title: homemade baby wipes
directions: You will need Bounty brand paper towels.

title: cheesy chops
directions: Place boneless pork chops in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan (trim fat off chops).
Salt and pepper the chops (seasoning salt optional) and add chicken with rice soup, undiluted.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese over chops.
Peel and slice potatoes to fill the pan.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups shredded cheese over potatoes. Pour cream of chicken or mushroom soup, undiluted, over cheese. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Take the foil off and bake for 1 hour or until the cheese is lightly brown.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread coconut on bottom of well-greased 15 x 11 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread pecans over coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix softened cream cheese, softened butter and sugar.
Drop spoonfuls into the batter (don't stir).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or check for doneness with toothpick.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs, flour, vanilla, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; stir until well blended.
Add apples; stir well. Add pecans; stir well.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour. Remove cake and sprinkle top with powdered sugar.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: bacon wrap-ups
directions: Melt
butter;
stir in stuffing mix.
Add egg and milk. Mix thoroughly.
Wrap
1 full teaspoon of stuffing mixture in 1/2 strip of bacon.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° until bacon cooks or about 30 minutes.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in small amount of fat.
Set aside to drain. Put sliced potatoes in casserole with onion, salt and pepper.
Lay browned pork chops on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in covered casserole.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and seasoning over low heat.
Stir until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Combine soaked beans with the remaining ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot all day and season to taste with salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce (garlic if you like).
Serve over rice.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle with 2 cups crushed cornflakes.
Pour 1/4 cup margarine evenly over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: carrot salad
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook and drain.
Combine other ingredients and pour over warm carrots.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: kolbasi and noodle supper
directions: Stir-fry the following in 3 Tbsp. butter until crisp-tender: onion, green pepper, mushrooms, vegetables, garlic powder and oregano.
Add Kolbasi and heat through.
Stir in the Parmesan cheese and serve over butter noodles with additional cheese. Serves 6-8.

title: eggplant parmesan(low-fat)
directions: Slice eggplant and place on baking sheet and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
(This draws moisture from eggplant so it won't absorb fat while frying.)

title: chicken fajita pizza
directions: Place pizza crust on pizza pan and partially bake (6 minutes) until lightly browned.
Remove from oven.
Heat olive oil in skillet and saute chicken breast, which has been cut into bite-size pieces, until browned.
Chop peppers.
Add peppers and seasonings to chicken and stir-fry until crisp-tender (2 minutes). Sprinkle chicken mixture on pizza crust and top with taco sauce and shredded cheese.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is slightly melted.
Cut in wedges and serve.

title: fireside supper
directions: Combine chicken, celery, 1/2 cup cheese, onion, lemon juice, salt, pepper and enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Mix lightly. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and chips. Continue baking until cheese is melted.

title: eva st.  clair's glazed sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Cook unpeeled sweet potatoes in water to cover until tender. Cool.
Peel and slice lengthwise in 1/2-inch slices.
Layer 1/2 of sweet potatoes in shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with apples.
Top with second layer of potatoes.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and water.
Bring to boil.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: tropical fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except fruit.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Sprinkle with additional coconut if desired.
Serve with fruit.

title: frozen pumpkin squares
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, coconut, ginger and butter until it crumbles.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Put in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir mixture and bake 5 more minutes. Crumble mixture and remove 1 1/2 cups from pan.
Pat remainder in pan and let cool.

title: fruit punch
directions: Make a syrup by combining water and sugar.
Boil 5 minutes; cool.
Combine thick syrup, fruit juices and ice water.
Pour over ice.
Garnish with mint leaves and slices of oranges and lemons. Yields 30 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine mashed potatoes, eggs, milk, white sugar, 3/4 stick margarine and spices; mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fig preserves
