directions: Add ingredients. Boil 3 minutes. Place in jelly jar and seal.

title: shrimp or tuna salad
directions: Dilute gelatin in cold water.
Heat soup and add to gelatin. Mix cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add to gelatin mixture. Add pepper, celery and meat.
Pour in casserole or ring mold. Chill.

title: golden autumn chowder
directions: Brown steak in oil; simmer for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until meat is tender.
All other ingredients are simmered in with the meat. Vegetables will not get mushy or fall apart due to the vinegar. Remove the bay leaf.
Serves 6.

title: white pull candy
directions: Oil a platter with vegetable oil.
Place the sugar, vinegar and butter in a deep saucepan.
Stir over low heat until the sugar is dissolved.

Increase heat slightly and cook without stirring, until a candy thermometer registers 268° or until a small quantity of the syrup will form a hard ball when dropped into a bowl of cold water. Remove pan from stove and add vanilla.
Stir only enough to blend mixture.
Pour candy onto platter.
Let cool until a dent can be made in it when pressed with finger.
Gather into a lump and pull it with finger tips until is light and porous.
Dip hands in cold water often to prevent sticking.
Roll into long thin strips and cut in 1-inch pieces.
Place in tight tin can if you want creamy.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter; add the sugar.
Combine other ingredients. Roll dough into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Mash ball flat with glass bottom that has been dipped in sugar. Place pecan half in center.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: puffy cheese and egg bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Butter an 8x8x2 baking dish. Cut each slice of bread into 4 triangles. Arrange triangles on the bottom of the dish. Beat eggs slightly; add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour mixture into baking dish. Bake, uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes. Cut into 6 pieces.

title: mango nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first five ingredients. In another bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla. Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fold in mangoes, dates and nuts (batter will be stiff). Spoon into 2 greased 8x4x2 inch loaf pans. Bake at 350 for 50-55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs, sugars and oil.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla; stir.
Add zucchini; stir.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: almond roca(candy)
directions: In
a
medium
saucepan, stir sugar and water, then add butter.
Cook
on
high
to
265° (hard boil stage; you need a candy
thermometer).
Add 2/3 of the almonds.
Stir constantly to 295° (hard crack stage).
Remove and pour into cookie sheet to cool.
Sprinkle
a large Hershey bar over the top and when melted, spread
around.
Sprinkle with the remaining almonds. Cool and break into pieces.

title: strawberry fruit pops
directions: In a small heatproof custard cup, sprinkle gelatin over cold water.
Stir and set aside for 10 minutes.
Place dish in a small pan of water and heat gently until gelatine mixture is completely dissolved.
Cool mixture.
Place strawberries in a medium bowl and sprinkle with sugar.
Stir gently and set aside for 15 minutes. Combine cooled gelatine mixture, strawberries with their juice, lemon juice and corn syrup.
Spoon into ice pop molds and freeze for at least 2 hours.
Makes about 6 fruit pops.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat 1 minute after each egg.
Carefully mix in food coloring.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and soda together.
Mix buttermilk with vinegar and vanilla.
Add to the creamed ingredients alternately with dry ingredients.
Beat on medium speed until well mixed.
Turn onto 2 greased waxed paper-lined 9-inch layer pans.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool and spread with icing.
Serves 24.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare dinner according to packaged directions. Add tuna, soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by teaspoonful in medium waffle iron. Bake for a minute or two.
Frost with Chocolate Frosting when cool.

title: bubbling butter sauce (for fish)
directions: Melt the butter and add all the ingredients.
Heat until bubbly.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.
This is a tasty sauce to brush on fish when broiling or cooking on the barbecue.

title: milkshakes
directions: Put in blender.
Mix at high speed.
For thick milkshake, mix a short time.
For thin milkshake, mix a long time.

title: egg nog
directions: In a large saucepan beat together sugar and egg yolks.
Add salt and stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats a spoon.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: shrimp thermidor
directions: Cut shrimp if
large and toss with 1 tablespoon sherry; set aside.
Melt
butter,
remove from heat and stir in flour, salt and paprika until smooth.
Gradually stir in light cream. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add
shrimp
and	the
rest of the sherry.
Put into baking dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through.
Serve over rice.

title: turnovers(method:  foil packet)
directions: Scrape out the center of both sides of an English muffin, taking care not to scrape a hole into the muffin.
Fill one half of muffin with your favorite sandwich or dessert filling.
Cover the filled half with the other half; butter both halves on the outside.
Wrap muffin in foil, using the drugstore wrap method. Place on coals for 3 to 5 minutes per side.

title: special individual cheesecakes
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well, about
to
15 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour
mixture
into
foil
lined
baking cups which have paper
separators.
Fill
about 3/4 full.
Bake for 40 minutes at 300°
Cheesecakes
will
rise,
but
will not brown.
Take out of oven
and cool for 5 minutes.
A hole will form in center
of cheesecakes.
Combine
sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla;
put
about
one
or two teaspoons of mixture into the hole that forms in each cheesecake. Add 1 teaspoon jelly
or
pie filling on top.
Return to oven and bake for 5 minutes.
Makes 24 cheesecakes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Wash squash and shred like cabbage, Add salt let set for 10 to 15 minutes.
Press or squeeze water out.
Shred or break up cheese.
Mix together squash and onions with enough crackers to hold patties together.
Form into patties and roll in remaining cracker crumbs.
Fry at low temperature.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Mix all together and place in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: deer summer sausage
directions: Mix together and form into rolls.
Wrap in foil (shiny side up).
Place in refrigerator for 48 hours.
Fork holes in bottom of foil and place in pan (with drainage rack-broiler pan from oven works good).
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Unwrap. Cool.
Re-wrap and freeze.
(We usually double this.)

title: fluffy 7 minute icing
directions: Combine egg whites, syrup and salt in top of double boiler, beating with egg beater until thoroughly mixed.
Place over rapidly boiling water.
Beat constantly for 7 minutes or until it stands in peaks.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.
Lemon juice may be added to make it less sweet.

title: graham bread
directions: Mix sugar and lard together.
Add egg; beat together.
Add sour milk, then graham flour with soda, salt and baking powder.
Add white flour until dough is stiff enough (approximately 1 1/2 cups). Bake in oven 1 hour at 350°.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Beat
egg
whites
stiff.
Cream butter and sugar well; add egg
yolks and cream well.	Fold in the whites.
Add flour and buttermilk	alternately.
Add flavoring and jam.
Bake in four layers at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple relish
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together; let stand 20 minutes. Drain.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients to vinegar mixture; boil 20 minutes longer.
Pack in jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Top with the crackers, then pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: noodles
directions: Combine eggs, water, salt and food coloring.
Gradually add flour to egg mixture.
Roll dough out thin and let dry 1 hour. Roll up dough like jelly roll and cut into thin strips.
Drop noodles into boiling chicken broth.
Cook about 20 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken and ribs
directions: Mix and baste over meat as it grills.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add tomatoes, beans and taco seasoning.
Let simmer until all ingredients are thoroughly hot. Serve over chips, topped with cheese and lettuce.
Add picante sauce to taste.
This recipe is easy and good!

title: rotel dip
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Put cheese in a large bowl and add Ro-Tel.
Put mixture in microwave until cheese melts.
Serve with Doritos, nacho chips or Fritos.
If you do not want to make a big amount of dip, you can half or quarter the recipe.

title: yogurt coffeecake
directions: In mixer, cream butter and brown sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Stir together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with yogurt. Blend well.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: In the top of a double boiler over boiling water, heat water, butter and vinegar.

title: coconut cake icing
directions: Mix sugar, water, cream of tartar and marshmallows in pan and boil 3 minutes.
Cover and beat egg whites.
Add to mix and beat 5 minutes.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix and bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican food
directions: Brown meat, season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Line
baking dish with tortillas, pour meat over.	Add Ranch Style beans over
this.
Put
a
layer
of	onions, then layer of cheese, then
cover with tortillas and pour soup over tortillas and Ro-Tel tomatoes
over that.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until beef is crumbly.
Add soup and water.
Mix well.
Cook until heated through.
Stir in sour cream and mushrooms.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine first five ingredients; stir over low heat until blended.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat, being careful not to mistake air bubbles for boiling, then boil slowly, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes (to soft ball stage).
Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate and vanilla until chocolate is melted, then turn into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan and cool.
Cut into squares and remove.

title: chicken spaghetti #2
directions: Saute vegetables; add soup, milk and chicken.
Add cheese and cook on low until warm.
Pour over noodles.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all except club soda.
Chill until very cold.
Add the club soda.

title: salmon loaf
directions: In small bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Stir in bread crumbs and egg.
Mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Place in greased quart baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Whisk first 6 ingredients in a large bowl. Add peas and next 3 ingredients, tossing to coat. Cover and chill at least two hours. Serve on a lettuce lined platter. Yield: 6 cups.

title: texas style chile
directions: In a heavy skillet, saute ground beef.
Add chili peppers and scallions.
Then add garlic, salt, pepper, hot sauce and kidney beans.
Add raw onions, if desired.
Stir and serve.
Leaves you breathless.

title: mock cabbage rolls
directions: Mix meat, eggs, rice, salt, pepper, parsley, onion, garlic salt together.
Shape into 2 inch balls.
Cut cabbage into slices. In a large pan or crock pot, place a layer of cabbage, then meat, repeat process.
Once all cabbage and meat are in, cover with sauerkraut and soup.
Simmer 5 or 6 hours.

title: asian long beans with hazelnuts
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.

Spread the hazelnuts on a baking sheet and toast in the oven for about 8 minutes, until fragrant. Transfer the hot nuts to a kitchen towel and rub them together vigorously to remove most of the skins.
Finely chop the nuts and set aside.

title: carolina apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, and eggs together.
Sift together dry ingredients and add vanilla and apples.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: In
saucepan
over
low heat melt chips with margarine. In mixer bowl beat chocolate in mixture with remaining ingredients, except
nuts, until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 35
to
minutes at 325° until center is set. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add oil and mix well. Stir in crackers and cover tightly. These are better if you let them set for a while so that the crackers soak up the oil and spices.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Stone dates; cut in small pieces.
Sprinkle soda over dates. Pour cup of boiling water over them; let cool.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, bay leaves, garlic, celery seed, 1 cup water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boiling.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Cool.
Place eggs in jar. Pour mixture over eggs. Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 days.
To serve, remove from liquid and cut lengthwise.
Makes 12 eggs.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Two parts of celery to one each of apples and nuts.
They must all be chopped very fine, well seasoned with salt, pepper and paprika.
Mix a little mayonnaise with them and sprinkle grated cheese over it.
It can be served on lettuce; an apple or orange basket may be used as a container.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Divide batter evenly among cups.
Bake until golden brown 15 to 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mashed bananas.
Stir in sour cream.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have a shallow 2 1/2-quart baking dish ready.
Beat eggs in a large bowl until blended.
Stir in cottage cheese and flour until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients until evenly distributed.
Spread in baking dish and bake 1 hour or until set and edges are golden brown.

title: chili spaghetti casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and place in prepared dish.

title: layered green salad
directions: Layer in order given.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Trim away the thick stalk of the cauliflower; chop the florets and small stems into pieces about 1/2 inch in diameter.
In a large saucepan, bring the stock to a boil.
Add the cauliflower; cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Let cool and puree in batches in a blender or food processor.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Roll out; cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Frost with a powdered sugar frosting.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Make 2 rolls, wrap in foil
and
chill overnight.
Slice very thin.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fast and filling tortellini dinner(serves 3 to 4)
directions: Cook tortellini according to package instructions.
Meanwhile, cook mushrooms in butter over medium heat until well cooked but not at all crunchy.
Drain tortellini.
Return to pot.
Dump in cheeses, mushrooms and ham.
Toss until Rondele is melted.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix with oil, water and eggs until thoroughly mixed.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta according to package directions, drain, rinse, and cool.
Place in large bowl.
Sprinkle salad supreme lightly, then mix.
Repeat until pasta is well covered.
Add tomatoes, onion, and cucumber.
Mix gently.
Pour on dressing.
Mix gently.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: vegetables and sausages in foil
directions: Preheat barbecue to medium-high; shape foil into basket.
Add carrots, onion and garlic butter.
Seal with another piece of foil and cook on grill for 30 minutes.
Remove top foil and add zucchini, green peppers and sausage.
Replace foil and cook on grill another 30 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain
and
chop water chestnuts.
Place vegetables and chestnuts in
a
large
bowl.
Add chicken soup, onion, celery and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Pour into a 2 to 3 quart casserole dish. Top
with
cracker
crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes, until bubbly and crackers are browned.

title: down-home fried rice
directions: Heat oil in heavy casserole or wok over medium-low heat.
Add onion, celery, garlic and ginger.
Cook, stirring, 5 minutes.
Add bell pepper and cook 3 minutes more.
Add rice, beef broth and ham.
Cook, stirring, 2 minutes.
Add shrimp and snow peas; cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs and soy sauce together. Push rice to sides, making a well.
Return casserole to heat and pour egg mixture in center.
Stir with fork 1 minute, until eggs are set.
Gently fold in rice; heat through.
Stir in green onion.

title: pumpkin mousse
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook beef, salt, pepper, celery, onion and green pepper until tender and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes. Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: shaker bean soup
directions: Sort and rinse beans; place in a Dutch oven, cover with water and bring to boil; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand for 1 hour.
Drain beans and discard liquid.
Return beans to pan; add meat and 3 quarts of water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until meat easily falls from the bone.
Remove and trim meat from bones; discard bones, return meat to pan and add onion, celery, carrots, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until beans are tender. Add tomatoes and brown sugar and cook an additional 10 minutes. Just before serving, add spinach.
Yield: 5 quarts.

title: lemon broiled fish fillets
directions: Place fish in greased broiler pan.
Melt butter or margarine; mix with salt, pepper, worcestershire sauce and lemon juice. Brush fillets with this mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil 3 inches from source of heat for about 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn, brush again with sauce and sprinkle with paprika. Broil 7 minutes longer until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix with Cheddar cheese, then all other ingredients.
When all is well mixed, form into a ball and roll ball in sesame seed.
Ball will be soft.
Put in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: strawberry parfait
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix together all ingredients and add nuts. Refrigerate.

title: bran muffin mix
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Pour water over Shredded Wheat; mix in usual manner.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter will keep in refrigerator for a month. When oven is on for a casserole or something else, just add some raisins, dates or nuts.
They are nutty flavored and handy to have muffin mix on hand.

title: homemade bread
directions: Heat milk, water, sugar, salt, shortening and oleo until warm. Off heat, add the yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add flour, 2 cups at a time, and mix until dough pulls away from bowl and you can handle.

title: debra's camp stew
directions: In a crock pot, mix together:
chicken, beef, pork, corn and tomatoes.
Add soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and black pepper. Mix well.
Add potatoes, mixing well.
Simmer 2 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Stir butter into hot spaghetti.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Put in buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Brown in skillet the sausage, onion and green pepper; drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: healthy bologna
directions: Mix real well, then stuff into bags, making sure there are no air pockets.
Hang up 3 days, then smoke with liquid smoke.
Smoke again in 2 weeks.
Meat can also be ground coarsely before seasonings are added, then ground finely afterwards.

title: boiled peanuts
directions: Place peanuts into large stock pot.
Cover with water.
Add Hawaiian salt and five spice.
Bring to rolling boil.
Start timer (25 to 30 minutes) when water is at rolling boil.
Turn stove off after 25 to 30 minutes.
Leave peanuts in pot until all of them sink to bottom of pot.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Drain clams and reserve juice.
Boil linguine in salted water. Spoon olive oil over moderate heat in saucepan.
Add shallots and saute 3 minutes.
Stir in garlic, oregano and hot pepper.
Cook 30 seconds.
Stir in flour for 10 seconds.
Pour in wine and 2/3 cup of clam juice.
Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Add clams with 1/4 cup of parsley and Parmesan.
Stir in butter and remove from heat.
Toss pasta with sauce.

title: chocolate walnut brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, combine butter and sugar. In a separate bowl, mix flour, salt and baking soda, then add to the butter mixture.
Stir together, then add in almond extract, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan; pour the batter in and place in the oven for 40 minutes.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Sift flour and salt together; cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour gradually until well blended.
Add melted chocolate and mix.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble and microwave ground beef on High for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Top with onion, salt, pepper and Tater Tots.
Combine both cans of soup and pour over beef mixture. Microwave on High for 15 minutes. Do not cover.

title: *real french onion soup
directions: Boil 6 cups water and dissolve bouillon cubes.
In a Dutch oven or large pan, brown butter lightly.
Add sliced onions and brown.
Add the 6 cups of beef stock and the salt and pepper. Also add dashes of other optional ingredients mentioned.
Taste as you go!
It gets better and better.
Boil for 10 minutes.

title: firecracker burgers
directions: Combine meat, chilies, bouillon and cayenne pepper.
Shape into 8 thin patties.
Grill or broil patties and onion slice 3 to 5 minutes on each side.
Place hamburger on bun, top with cheese, onion, second patty, tomato and pickle slice.
Serve with mustard and ketchup or mayonnaise if desired.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake in 375° oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy quiche
directions: In blender, mix eggs, biscuit mix, milk and melted butter. Blend well.
Pour into pie or quiche pan.
Sprinkle cheese, ham and onion over egg mixture and push in gently.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: dill and rye dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except bread.
Slice the top off the bread and hollow out the loaf, reserving the pieces of bread to use as dippers.
Fill bread with dip.
Serve surrounded by raw vegetables and pieces of bread for dipping.

title: grilled steaks
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour over steak and let sit until ready to grill.

title: bbq
directions: Brown hamburger, drain fat.
Mix all ingredients with the hamburger.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix together and add potato chips last.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: zucchini frittata with marjoram
directions: Toss the zucchini with 1 teaspoon salt and set it aside in a colander for 20 to 30 minutes.
Rinse briefly, then squeeze dry. Warm half the oil in a wide skillet over medium-high heat.
Add the zucchini and cook, stirring frequently, until it is dry and flecked with gold in a few places, about 6 minutes.
Transfer the zucchini to a bowl and wipe out the pan.
Preheat the broiler.
Beat the eggs with a few pinches of salt and some pepper, then stir in the garlic, zucchini, marjoram and cheese.
Add the remaining oil to the pan and, when it is hot, add the eggs.
Lower the heat, cook for a minute or so, then give the pan a few jerks to make sure the eggs are loose on the bottom.
If they are sticking, loosen them carefully with a thin rubber spatula.
Cook over medium-low heat until the eggs start to set.
Add a little more freshly grated Parmesan on top.
Put the frittata 4 to 6 inches under the broiler to finish cooking the top.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix orange jello, boiling water, mandarin oranges and juice and crushed pineapple and juice.
Put in refrigerator until hard.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Pour sugar on and let set 1 hour (overnight works good).
Chop or grind the onion, pepper and celery.
Add all ingredients to kraut and refrigerate.
Can be frozen and still taste good.

title: aggie's apple cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup butter, 1 teaspoon of sugar, baking powder, salt and 1 1/4 cups of flour together.
Then add beaten egg yolk and milk.
Pat into coffee cake pan.
Top the dough with apples covered with 3/4 cup sugar, cinnamon, 1 1/2 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes and at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Mix lemon-lime soda and apple juice.
Float lemon slices on top.
(This recipe may be doubled.)

title: canned hot peppers
directions: Fry pepper strips in hot oil.
Salt to taste.
When they begin to shrink, pack them into jars about 2/3 full.
Finish filling with tomato sauce and cold pack about 20 minutes.
Homemade tomato sauce is better.

title: crazy cake
directions: Blend flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt together in 9 x 13 cake pan. Make 3 holes in dry ingredients; pour oil into each hole. Add vanilla to each hole. Pour water all over and mix with fork until smooth. Do not beat. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffing (apple raisin)
directions: Place raisins in boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and add soft bread.
Saute 3 minutes.
Add onion, garlic and celery in butter.
Add to bread mixture with apple, parsley, salt and paprika.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and margarine.
Cook until boiling.
Remove from heat, add soda and vanilla.
Let cool for 5 minutes or to touch.
Pour over popcorn.
Oil hands to form into balls.
Cool and wrap in wax paper.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat chocolate and shortening over low heat, stirring until melted.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a greased pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: homemade sloppy joes
directions: Simmer ingredients in a large nonstick skillet for 1 hour.
You can also cook this in a crock-pot for 4 to 5 hours while you are away from the house.
Have your butcher grind white turkey meat for you and you will save a lot of fat grams.
Serves 8.

title: quick potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix salad dressing, potatoes, cheese, soup, onion and pepper. Spoon into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with combined cornflakes and margarine.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: sour cream rhubarb pie
directions: Put rhubarb in pie shell.
Mix sour cream, sugar, flour or tapioca and egg yolks.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Spread over pie and bake until light brown, not burned.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix together; blend well.
Preheat frying pan and melt enough bacon drippings to cover lightly the bottom of the pan.
Two tablespoons mixture makes a nice size pancake.
Cook over medium heat until golden brown.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Season hamburger with salt, pepper and garlic.
Brown and drain completely.
Soften tortillas in hot oil.
Place 1 to 2 tablespoons meat in center with 1 tablespoon of sour cream.
Roll up and place in baking pan.
When all are done, cover with sauce, then top with cheese and sprinkle with onions.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until bubbles.

title: delicious salad
directions: Chop and mix vegetables.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine juice, flour, sugar, pineapple and cheese.
Mix well and put in a 1-quart greased casserole dish.
Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are slightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees until hot.

title: surprise apple bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add beaten eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and applesauce.
Stir all ingredients.
Add apples, nuts and raisins.
Put into 2 loaf pans (greased).
Press a cherry into each pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain and rinse.
Put in a large bowl.
Drain and slice hearts of palm.
Add to pasta.
Drain sliced black olives and add to pasta.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Pour dressing over pasta. Toss to cover.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and noodles casserole
directions: Cook noodles. Drain. Add butter, milk, soup and chicken, chopped.
Mix.
Let simmer 10 minutes. Serve.

title: carob cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine liquid ingredients.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry and stir.
Pour into cake pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: snitzel beans
directions: Fry bacon and drain off most of the grease.
Add onion and pepper and cook down.
Add green beans and simmer.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms and cook on low to medium heat about 1 hour.

title: steamed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and put in large stock pot.
Pour beer over mushrooms and cook on low heat, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring frequently.
You may add in lemon juice and more beer as needed, always keeping about an inch of liquid in pan.
Season with fresh ground pepper.

title: fettuccine alfredo with broccoli and tomatoes
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
About 3 minutes before it is done, add broccoli florets and cook until both are firm and tender. Remove from heat.

Ladle out and reserve 1/3 cup cooking liquid from pot. Drain pasta and broccoli in a colander. Mix sour cream, Parmesan and reserved liquid in pot or serving bowl. Add pasta, broccoli and cherry tomatoes. Toss to coat well.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Cut marshmallows in quarters and mix with rhubarb.
Add sugar and arrange in 8-inch square pan.
Pour cake batter over.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Roll out on floured surface and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° until bottoms are light brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pumpkin casserole
directions: Cut lid of pumpkin as for jack-o-lantern; clean out inside. Put lid on pumpkin.
Place on cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pumpkin should remain firm.
While baking put together the remaining ingredients.

title: pasta and peas with ham
directions: Saute onions and ham in olive oil until onions are soft.
Add sweet peas with liquid to oil, add tomato sauce and mix.
Let cook 15 minutes over low heat.
Cook ditalini, drain.
Mix half with peas.
Serve.
Add cheese to taste.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Cook pork roast for 5 hours; debone meat and add to sauce. Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Reheat the next day.
Get very hot.

title: pecan treats
directions: Beat sugar and whites to soft peak form.
Fold in pecans. Pour pecans on cookie sheet.
Dot butter over pecan mixture. Place in a 300° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove and stir.
Return to oven.
Do this 4 times.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red beans, rice and sausage
directions: Cook all on medium heat.
Cook 1 cup rice and 1 cup water (if using Minute rice, add rice to boiling water).
After rice is done, add to cooked mixture.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Prepare jello per package directions.

Refrigerate until partially set. Whip milk until thick. Add sugar, thickened jello and lemon juice. Sprinkle 1/2 of crushed cookies on bottom of 9 x 12 pan. Pour the jello mixture over the cookies. Sprinkle remaining crushed cookies over the jello mixture. Chill in refrigerator 1 hour before serving (or overnight). Cut in squares. Optional:
Top with fresh fruit (strawberries, blueberries, raspberries).

title: grandma mary's rolls
directions: Scald milk; add margarine, mashed potatoes and egg (I use blender).
Add sugar, salt and yeast mixture.
Beat in 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Add rest of flour.
Knead well.
Let rise until double. Can punch down and let rise again if you have time.
Form in small balls and dip into melted shortening and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let rise at least 1 hour in warm place.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes, until golden.
Makes 20 to 24 rolls.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix and put in pie dish.
Top with chopped lettuce, tomatoes and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot venison chili
directions: Brown bacon and drain browned venison in bacon grease with onion and garlic.
Combine all ingredients except the fresh and pickled peppers in a large pot and bring to simmer.
Chop peppers and saute in bacon grease until tender; drain and add to meat. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve next day.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add dry cake mix, 1/3 at a time, mixing well after each addition. Cover; chill 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop by scant teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix altogether.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until set.

title: impossibly easy quesadilla pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Spray pie plate with cooking spray. Melt butter in 10-inch skillet. Cook onion in butter, stirring, until tender. Remove from heat. Stir in tomato, chilies, olives, 1 cup of cheese, cumin and salt. Spread in pie plate. Stir Bisquick, milk and eggs until blended and pour over vegetable mixture. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of cheese. Bake 3 to 5 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting. Serves 6.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together corn, sugar, flour, salt, pepper, melted oleo, egg yolks and milk in medium size casserole.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: date nut cake(diabetic)
directions: Mix oleo, eggs, sweetener, vanilla, cinnamon and cloves until creamy.
Add flour to mixture.
Fold in dates, nuts and applesauce.
Mix again.
Pour into lightly greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° until tests done.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, eggs and butter.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
The batter will be lumpy.
Spoon batter into twelve 2 1/2 inch greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until tops spring back when touched. Makes 12 muffins.

title: almond bark treats
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter in double boiler.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Pour almond bark and peanut butter mixture over top of dry mixture.
Drop onto waxed paper by teaspoon.

title: butter icing
directions: Beat until smooth.
Good on apple cake.

title: easy potatoes au gratin
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Layer with thin white sauce and Velveeta cheese.
Cover and cook on low until done.
(This works only in Silverstone saucepan, otherwise, put in greased casserole and bake in a 325° oven, covered, until done.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 of the cheese, sour cream, chicken soup, oleo and onion.
Pour over the potatoes and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Don't overcook. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix all together.
Beat with mixer about 10 minutes on medium speed.
Makes four 9-inch layers or three 10-inch layers.
Bake at 350° for about 25 or 30 minutes.
Cool layers and ice.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Fry sausage and onions, breaking sausage into small pieces, until brown.
Drain.
Drain sauerkraut and squeeze dry.
Add to sausage mixture with 1/4 cup bread crumbs, cream cheese, parsley, mustard, salt and pepper. Mix well and chill overnight.
Place flour for coating balls in a pie plate.
Place eggs and 2 tablespoons water in shallow bowl, beating lightly to combine.

title: zucchini chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
In a separate bowl add all the other ingredients except the walnuts and chocolate chips.
Slowly blend in with the egg mixture.
Add walnuts and chocolate chips. Grease cake pan and pour into a 9 x 13-inch loaf cake pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan to finish cooling.

title: citrus rice salad
directions: Drain oranges, reserving juice.
Mix juice, water, raisins and spices in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; stir in rice and return to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 6 minutes.
Spread rice mixture in a shallow pan; freeze for 10 minutes to quickly cool rice.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Makes 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine and peanut butter until smooth. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll mixture into balls; refrigerate for an additional 2 hours.

title: reunion casserole
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown the beef, sausage and onion. Drain off fat.
Stir in 1 cup cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken fruit and nut salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: french bread
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Add oil, 1/2 cup
sugar and salt.
Stir to dissolve.
Slowly add flour. Dough should be soft, but not sticky.
Let raise for 1 hour. Divide into 5 or 6 equal portions.
Let dough rest 10 minutes. Roll each piece into a 12 x 15-inch rectangle.
Cut with kitchen scissors every inch or 1 1/2 inches.
Brush with egg white and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let raise until double.
You can usually get two loaves on 1 jelly roll pan.
Keep to each side so the sides don't bake together.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: eastern shore sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, shortening, sugar and salt.
Add flour and baking powder.
Allow to rest 1 hour before making in biscuits.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 12 or 15 minutes.

title: orange crush salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and garnish with mandarin orange slices. Chill before serving.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and spread on cookie sheet. Cover with foil and put in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in squares and roll in flour.
Return to greased pan.
Combine soup and water; pour over meat.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Reduce heat to 325° and remove foil.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Make up one recipe of cornbread and bake.
Boil 4 to 6 pieces chicken in water until tender.
Take off bone.
Save broth.
Cut up onions and celery.
Boil in small amount of water until tender or cook in microwave with small amount of water about 8 minutes or so. Beat eggs well.
Add broth to breads to soften.
Add all ingredients together.
Grease a large baking dish with butter or spray with Pam.
Bake at 350° until brown and knife comes out clean.
Halve recipe to make smaller amount.
